name: Buzz
description: A light, crisp and bitter IPA brewed with English and American hops. A small batch brewed only once.
ingredients: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich Fuggles, First Gold, Fuggles, First Gold, Cascade Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Spicy chicken tikka masala, Grilled chicken quesadilla, Caramel toffee cake
malts: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich
hops: Fuggles, First Gold, Fuggles, First Gold, Cascade

name: Trashy Blonde
description: A titillating, neurotic, peroxide punk of a Pale Ale. Combining attitude, style, substance, and a little bit of low self esteem for good measure; what would your mother say? The seductive lure of the sassy passion fruit hop proves too much to resist. All that is even before we get onto the fact that there are no additives, preservatives, pasteurization or strings attached. All wrapped up with the customary BrewDog bite and imaginative twist.
ingredients: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich Amarillo, Simcoe, Amarillo, Motueka Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Fresh crab with lemon, Garlic butter dipping sauce, Goats cheese salad, Creamy lemon bar doused in powdered sugar
malts: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich
hops: Amarillo, Simcoe, Amarillo, Motueka

name: Berliner Weisse With Yuzu - B-Sides
description: Japanese citrus fruit intensifies the sour nature of this German classic.
ingredients: Propino Pale Malt, Wheat Malt, Propino Pale Malt for kettle souring, Acidulated Malt for kettle souring Bramling Cross Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Smoked chicken wings, Miso ramen, Yuzu cheesecake
malts: Propino Pale Malt, Wheat Malt, Propino Pale Malt for kettle souring, Acidulated Malt for kettle souring
hops: Bramling Cross

name: Pilsen Lager
description: Our Unleash the Yeast series was an epic experiment into the differences in aroma and flavour provided by switching up your yeast. We brewed up a wort with a light caramel note and some toasty biscuit flavour, and hopped it with Amarillo and Centennial for a citrusy bitterness. Everything else is down to the yeast. Pilsner yeast ferments with no fruity esters or spicy phenols, although it can add a hint of butterscotch.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Munich Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo Wyeast 2007 - Pilsen Lager™
food_pairing: Spicy crab cakes, Spicy cucumber and carrot Thai salad, Sweet filled dumplings
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Munich
hops: Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo

name: Avery Brown Dredge
description: An Imperial Pilsner in collaboration with beer writers. Tradition. Homage. Revolution. We wanted to showcase the awesome backbone of the Czech brewing tradition, the noble Saaz hop, and also tip our hats to the modern beers that rock our world, and the people who make them.
ingredients: Lager Malt, Wheat Saaz, Saaz, Saaz Wyeast 2007 - Pilsen Lager™
food_pairing: Vietnamese squid salad, Chargrilled corn on the cob with paprika butter, Strawberry and rhubarb pie
malts: Lager Malt, Wheat
hops: Saaz, Saaz, Saaz

name: Electric India
description: Re-brewed as a spring seasonal, this beer – which appeared originally as an Equity Punk shareholder creation – retains its trademark spicy, fruity edge. A perfect blend of Belgian Saison and US IPA, crushed peppercorns and heather honey are also added to produce a genuinely unique beer.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Munich, Wheat Amarillo, Nelson Sauvin, Amarillo, Peppercorns, Nelson Sauvin, Amarillo Wyeast 3711 - French Saison™
food_pairing: Mussels with a garlic and herb sauce, Crab melt sandwich, Shortbread cookies
malts: Extra Pale, Munich, Wheat
hops: Amarillo, Nelson Sauvin, Amarillo, Peppercorns, Nelson Sauvin, Amarillo

name: AB:12
description: An Imperial Black Belgian Ale aged in old Invergordon Scotch whisky barrels with mountains of raspberries, tayberries and blackberries in each cask. Decadent but light and dry, this beer would make a fantastic base for ageing on pretty much any dark fruit - we used raspberries, tayberries and blackberries beause they were local.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Chocolate, Carafa Special Malt Type 3 Tomahawk, Magnum, Magnum, Tomahawk, Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo, Tomahawk Wyeast 3522 - Belgian Ardennes™
food_pairing: Tandoori lamb with pomegranate, Beef Wellington with a red wine jus, Raspberry chocolate torte
malts: Extra Pale, Chocolate, Carafa Special Malt Type 3
hops: Tomahawk, Magnum, Magnum, Tomahawk, Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo, Tomahawk

name: Fake Lager
description: Fake is the new black. Fake is where it is at. Fake Art, fake brands, fake breasts, and fake lager. We want to play our part in the ugly fallout from the Lager Dream. Say hello to Fake Lager – a zesty, floral 21st century faux masterpiece with added BrewDog bitterness.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Munich, Caramalt, Acidulated Malt Magnum, Magnum, Hersbrucker, Saaz, Hersbrucker, Saaz Wyeast 2007 - Pilsen Lager™
food_pairing: Fried crab cakes with avocado salsa, Spicy shredded pork roll with hot dipping sauce, Key lime pie
malts: Extra Pale, Munich, Caramalt, Acidulated Malt
hops: Magnum, Magnum, Hersbrucker, Saaz, Hersbrucker, Saaz

name: AB:07
description: Whisky cask-aged imperial scotch ale. Beer perfect for when the rain is coming sideways. Liquorice, plum and raisin temper the warming alcohol, producing a beer capable of holding back the Scottish chill.
ingredients: Munich, Flaked Oats, Wheat, Caramalt, Crystal, Dark Crystal, Chocolate, Peated Malt, Amber, Brown Saaz, First Gold Saflager S189
food_pairing: Kedgeree, Scotch broth with sourdough bread, Clootie dumpling
malts: Munich, Flaked Oats, Wheat, Caramalt, Crystal, Dark Crystal, Chocolate, Peated Malt, Amber, Brown
hops: Saaz, First Gold

name: Bramling X
description: Good old Bramling Cross is elegant, refined, assured, (boring) and understated. Understated that is unless you hop the living daylights out of a beer with it. This is Bramling Cross re-invented and re-imagined, and shows just what can be done with English hops if you use enough of them. Poor Bramling Cross normally gets lost in a woeful stream of conformist brown ales made by sleepy cask ale brewers. But not anymore. This beer shows that British hops do have some soul, and is a fruity riot of blackberries, pears, and plums. Reminds me of the bramble, apple and ginger jam my grandmother used to make.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Crystal 150, Caramalt Bramling Cross, Bramling Cross Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Warm blackberry pie, Vinegar doused fish and chips, Aromatic korma curry with lemon and garlic naan
malts: Extra Pale, Crystal 150, Caramalt
hops: Bramling Cross, Bramling Cross

name: Misspent Youth
description: The brainchild of our small batch brewer, George Woods. A dangerously drinkable milk sugar- infused Scotch Ale.
ingredients: Pale Ale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Smoked Weyermann, Flaked Oats, Brown, Amber, Chocolate, Munich, Crystal 150 First Gold, Fuggles, Honey, Lactose, First Gold, Fuggles Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Roasted garlic and chilli infused camembert cheese, Korean style chicken wings, Chocolate milk shake
malts: Pale Ale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Smoked Weyermann, Flaked Oats, Brown, Amber, Chocolate, Munich, Crystal 150
hops: First Gold, Fuggles, Honey, Lactose, First Gold, Fuggles

name: Arcade Nation
description: Running the knife-edge between an India Pale Ale and a Stout, this particular style is one we truly love. Black IPAs are a great showcase for the skill of our brew team, balancing so many complex and twisting flavours in the same moment. The citrus, mango and pine from the hops – three of our all-time favourites – play off against the roasty dryness from the malt bill at each and every turn.
ingredients: Pale Ale, Caramalt, Crystal 150, Carafa Special Malt Type 1 Simcoe, Simcoe, Simcoe, Amarillo, Citra, Simcoe, Amarillo, Citra Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: King prawn kebabs, Halibut with a mango and tomato salad, Mint chocloate ice cream
malts: Pale Ale, Caramalt, Crystal 150, Carafa Special Malt Type 1
hops: Simcoe, Simcoe, Simcoe, Amarillo, Citra, Simcoe, Amarillo, Citra

name: Movember
description: A deliciously robust, black malted beer with a decadent dark, dry cocoa flavour that provides an enticing backdrop to the Cascade hops.
ingredients: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Carafa Special Malt Type 3 Cascade, Cascade, Cascade Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Vegetable egg scramble, Margherita pizza, Fresh berry crisp tart
malts: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Carafa Special Malt Type 3
hops: Cascade, Cascade, Cascade

name: Alpha Dog
description: A fusion of caramel malt flavours and punchy New Zealand hops. A session beer you can get your teeth into.
ingredients: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich, Crystal 150, Dark Crystal 350-400 Nelson Sauvin, Amarillo, Nelson Sauvin Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Pastrami, Swiss and horseradish sandwich, Sharp cheddar cheese and onion/ raisin chutney, Peanut brittle
malts: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich, Crystal 150, Dark Crystal 350-400
hops: Nelson Sauvin, Amarillo, Nelson Sauvin

name: Mixtape 8
tagline: An Epic Fusion Of Old Belgian, American New Wave, And Scotch Whisky.
description: This recipe is for the Belgian Tripel base. A blend of two huge oak aged beers – half a hopped up Belgian Tripel, and half a Triple India Pale Ale. Both aged in single grain whisky barrels for two years and blended, each beer brings its own character to the mix. The Belgian Tripel comes loaded with complex spicy, fruity esters, and punchy citrus hop character.
ingredients: Pale Ale - Tipple, Caramalt, Crystal Columbus Extract, Centennial, Cascade, Simcoe Wyeast 3522 - Belgian Ardennes™
food_pairing: Coriander & chilli crab cakes, Goats cheese salad with walnuts, radish and blood orange, Pistachio cake
malts: Pale Ale - Tipple, Caramalt, Crystal
hops: Columbus Extract, Centennial, Cascade, Simcoe

name: Libertine Porter
description: An avalanche of cross-continental hop varieties give this porter a complex spicy, resinous and citrusy aroma, with a huge malt bill providing a complex roasty counterpoint. Digging deeper into the flavour draws out cinder toffee, bitter chocolate and hints of woodsmoke.
ingredients: Extra Pale - Spring Blend, Caramalt, Crystal 150, Chocolate, Roasted Barley, Wheat, Flaked Oats, Smoked Malt Columbus, Columbus, Willamette, Galena, Columbus, Galena, Simcoe Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Blue cheese beef burger, Glazed short ribs, Chocolate cake
malts: Extra Pale - Spring Blend, Caramalt, Crystal 150, Chocolate, Roasted Barley, Wheat, Flaked Oats, Smoked Malt
hops: Columbus, Columbus, Willamette, Galena, Columbus, Galena, Simcoe

name: AB:06
description: Our sixth Abstrakt, this imperial black IPA combined dark malts with a monumental triple dry-hop, using an all-star team of some of our favourite American hops. Roasty and resinous.
ingredients: Pale Ale, Crystal 150, Caramalt, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Carafa Special Malt Type 3 Hop Extract, Amarillo, Chinook, Cascade, Centennial, Columbus, Chinook, Cascade, Centennial, Columbus, Amarillo Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Coffee dusted venison loin, Memphis-style beef short ribs, Chocolate orange brownies
malts: Pale Ale, Crystal 150, Caramalt, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Carafa Special Malt Type 3
hops: Hop Extract, Amarillo, Chinook, Cascade, Centennial, Columbus, Chinook, Cascade, Centennial, Columbus, Amarillo

name: Russian Doll – India Pale Ale
description: The levels of hops vary throughout the range. We love hops, so all four beers are big, bitter badasses, but by tweaking the amount of each hop used later in the boil and during dry- hopping, we can balance the malty backbone with some unexpected flavours. Simcoe is used in the whirlpool for all four beers, and yet still lends different characters to each
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal Cascade, Centennial, Simcoe, Simcoe, Citra, Simcoe, Cascade, Centennial, Citra Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Spicy chicken skewers, Fish tacos with hot sauce, Lemon pound cake with a ice sugar glaze
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal
hops: Cascade, Centennial, Simcoe, Simcoe, Citra, Simcoe, Cascade, Centennial, Citra

name: Hello My Name Is Mette-Marit
description: We sent this beer to Norway where it was known as 'Hello, my name is Censored’. You can make up your own mind as to why. This brew was a red berry explosion, with a reisnous bitter edge layered with dry berry tartness.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt Tomahawk, Motueka, Galena, Mt.Hood, Challenger, Galena, Nelson Sauvin Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Fårikål (mutton stew) with a spicy twist, Fenalår (salted cured lamb), Krumkake with lingonberry jam
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt
hops: Tomahawk, Motueka, Galena, Mt.Hood, Challenger, Galena, Nelson Sauvin

name: Rabiator
description: Imperial Wheat beer / Weizenbock brewed by a homesick German in leather trousers. Think banana bread, bubble gum and David Hasselhoff.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Wheat, Crystal Columbus, Hersbrucker Wyeast 3333 - German Wheat™
food_pairing: Grilled portabello mushroom burger, Chicken sausages with creamy mash, Caramel and banana meringue pie
malts: Extra Pale, Wheat, Crystal
hops: Columbus, Hersbrucker

name: Vice Bier
description: Our take on the classic German Kristallweizen. A clear German wheat beer, layers of bubblegum and vanilla perfectly balanced with the American and New Zealand hops.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Wheat, Caramalt Waimea, Amarillo, Nelson Sauvin, Motueka, Simcoe, Citra, Waimea Wyeast 3638 - Bavarian Wheat™
food_pairing: Citrus salad with balsamic dressing, Lobster, Ginger and orange cookies
malts: Extra Pale, Wheat, Caramalt
hops: Waimea, Amarillo, Nelson Sauvin, Motueka, Simcoe, Citra, Waimea

name: Devine Rebel (w/ Mikkeller)
description: Two of Europe's most experimental, boundary-pushing brewers, BrewDog and Mikkeller, combined forces to produce a rebellious beer that combined their respective talents and brewing skills. The 12.5% Barley Wine fermented well, and the champagne yeast drew it ever closer to 12.5%. The beer was brewed with a single hop variety and was going to be partially aged in oak casks.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich, Amber Nelson Sauvin, Nelson Sauvin Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Stilton on gingerbread biscuits, Pot roasted artichokes, Lamb chops with caramelised figs
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich, Amber
hops: Nelson Sauvin, Nelson Sauvin

name: Storm
description: Dark and powerful Islay magic infuses this tropical sensation of an IPA. Using the original Punk IPA as a base, we boosted the ABV to 8% giving it some extra backbone to stand up to the peated smoke imported directly from Islay.
ingredients: Extra Pale Ahtanum, Chinook, Crystal, Chinook, Ahtanum, Chinook, Crystal, Motueka Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Oysters, Hickory smoked ham, Rocky Road
malts: Extra Pale
hops: Ahtanum, Chinook, Crystal, Chinook, Ahtanum, Chinook, Crystal, Motueka

name: The End Of History
description: The End of History: The name derives from the famous work of philosopher Francis Fukuyama, this is to beer what democracy is to history. Complexity defined. Floral, grapefruit, caramel and cloves are intensified by boozy heat.
ingredients: Extra Pale Nelson Sauvin, Centennial, Nelson Sauvin, Amarillo, Centennial Wyeast 3522 - Belgian Ardennes™
food_pairing: Roasted wood pigeon with black pudding, Pan seared venison fillet with juniper sauce, Apricot coconut cake
malts: Extra Pale
hops: Nelson Sauvin, Centennial, Nelson Sauvin, Amarillo, Centennial

name: Bad Pixie
description: 2008 Prototype beer, a 4.7% wheat ale with crushed juniper berries and citrus peel.
ingredients: Wheat, Extra Pale First Gold, First Gold, Sorachi Ace Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Poached sole fillet with capers, Summer fruit salad, Banana split
malts: Wheat, Extra Pale
hops: First Gold, First Gold, Sorachi Ace

name: Skull Candy
description: The first beer that we brewed on our newly commissioned 5000 litre brewhouse in Fraserburgh 2009. A beer with the malt and body of an English bitter, but the heart and soul of vibrant citrus US hops.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 120 Cascade, Cascade, Centennial, Amarillo, Simcoe Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Haggis bon bons, Rosemary and lemon roast chicken, Oatmeal and cranberry cookies
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 120
hops: Cascade, Cascade, Centennial, Amarillo, Simcoe

name: Dog B
description: Our anniversary stout was based on AB:04, one of our most sought after beers ever. This beer is slightly different each year, with subtle variations coming into play purely down to environmental and fermentation factors. What doesn't change is the rich dark chocolate, bitter coffee and chilli warmth of this monumental Stout.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Wheat, Flaked Oats, Dark Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Honey Chinook, Cascade, Fuggles, Coffee, Fuggles, Coffee Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Blackened cajun beef, Blue cheese, Flourless chocolate cheesecake
malts: Extra Pale, Wheat, Flaked Oats, Dark Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Honey
hops: Chinook, Cascade, Fuggles, Coffee, Fuggles, Coffee

name: HBC 369
description: HBC 369 brings rich fruity flavours with the tiniest layer of candy coating on top. HBC 369 (the hop) can bring notes of blueberries, pear, and possibly even sweet potato. HBC 369 (the beer) was balanced, with just one hop providing a complex aroma, and a dry bitterness.
ingredients: Extra Pale - Spring Blend, Caramalt, Crystal 150 HBC 369, HBC 369, HBC 369 Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Spicy jalapeño & seared steak fajitas, Grilled spicy corn with feta crumbles, Blueberry pie
malts: Extra Pale - Spring Blend, Caramalt, Crystal 150
hops: HBC 369, HBC 369, HBC 369

name: 10 Heads High
description: 10 Heads High is loosely based on our awesome 2011 Prototype beer Hops Kill Nazis. This is an uncompromising 7.8% Imperial Red Ale loaded high with American Hops. Think of this as an Imperial India Red Ale, or a super-charged version of 5am Saint. Either way this is a seriously good beer!
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150, Dark Crystal Chinook, Chinook, Centennial, Chinook, Centennial, Chinook Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Arrabiata pasta, Mulled cheddar, Toasted almond cake
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150, Dark Crystal
hops: Chinook, Chinook, Centennial, Chinook, Centennial, Chinook

name: Dana - IPA Is Dead
description: Hailing from Slovenia, Dana was originally cross bred from the German Hallertau Magnum and native Slovenian varieties. Like any good faux noble hop should, it infuses a rustic, musty spiciness into a toasty beast of a malt base.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Munich Dana, Dana, Dana, Dana Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Spicy Asian-style noodles, Smokey chipotle beef brisket tostada, Sweet potato pie
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Munich
hops: Dana, Dana, Dana, Dana

name: Nanny State
description: Brewing a full flavoured craft beer at 0.5% is no easy task. Packed with loads of Centennial, Amarillo, Columbus, Cascade and Simcoe hops, dry hopped to the brink and back and sitting at 55 IBUs, Nanny State is a force to be reckoned with. With a backbone of 8 different specialty malts, Nanny State will tantalise your taste buds and leave you yearning for more.
ingredients: Munich, Caramalt, Crystal 150, Amber, Dark Crystal, Chocolate, Wheat, Rye Amarillo, Simcoe, Centennial, Amarillo, Simcoe, Centennial, Amarillo, Simcoe, Cascade, Ahtanum, Centennial, Cascade, Ahtanum, Simcoe, Columbus Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Earthy mushroom pasta
malts: Munich, Caramalt, Crystal 150, Amber, Dark Crystal, Chocolate, Wheat, Rye
hops: Amarillo, Simcoe, Centennial, Amarillo, Simcoe, Centennial, Amarillo, Simcoe, Cascade, Ahtanum, Centennial, Cascade, Ahtanum, Simcoe, Columbus

name: AB:05
description: Belgian Imperial Stout aged on toasted coconut and cacao. The Belgian yeast strain introduces a whole new dimension to the Imperial Stout style resulting in a beer that resembles a marshmallow toasted on a smouldering barbeque then smothered in dark chocolate. Massively seductive and encapsulating this blacker than midnight beer pours with coffee brown head so thick you could almost stand on it, and with an epic lacing on your glass.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Flaked Oats, Pale Crystal, Dark Crystal First Gold, First Gold Wyeast 3522 - Belgian Ardennes™
food_pairing: Venison with cacao nibs, Apple upside-down cake, Toffee marshmallow pie
malts: Extra Pale, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Flaked Oats, Pale Crystal, Dark Crystal
hops: First Gold, First Gold

name: Sorachi Ace
description: A hop that tastes of bubble gum? Seriously? No, we did not believe it either. But it does! This is one unique, son of a bitch of a hop. Lemony, deep, musty with a smoothness that belies its power. This hop is lemony like a lemon who was angry earlier but is now tired because of all the rage. This hop of Japanese origin is best enjoyed trying to make sushi from your gold fish, or trying to persuade your girlfriend (or boyfriend maybe) to dress up as a Geisha for Valentine’s Day.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Crystal 150, Caramalt Sorachi Ace, Sorachi Ace Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Sashimi, Grilled salmon with a herb and citrus infused butter, Basil, lemon and pine nut angel hair pasta with grilled chicken
malts: Extra Pale, Crystal 150, Caramalt
hops: Sorachi Ace, Sorachi Ace

name: Bourbon Baby
description: Santa Paws Scotch ale aged in bourbon barrels - light, dry and toasty, with vanilla, hints of chocolate and ginger biscuit, and a faint spicy hoppiness.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Munich, Dark Crystal, Wheat, Flaked Oats, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Amber, Weyermann Beech Smoked First Gold, Willamette, Hallertauer Mittelfrüh Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Blackened cajun beef, Pulled pork, Millionaire's shortbread
malts: Extra Pale, Munich, Dark Crystal, Wheat, Flaked Oats, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Amber, Weyermann Beech Smoked
hops: First Gold, Willamette, Hallertauer Mittelfrüh

name: Berliner Weisse With Raspberries And Rhubarb - B-Sides
description: Tart, dry and acidic with a punch of summer berry as rhubarb crumble.
ingredients: Propino Pale Malt, Wheat Malt, Propino Pale Malt for kettle souring, Acidulated Malt for kettle souring Bramling Cross Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Grilled salmon, Mac and cheese fries, Cheesecake with raspberry coulis
malts: Propino Pale Malt, Wheat Malt, Propino Pale Malt for kettle souring, Acidulated Malt for kettle souring
hops: Bramling Cross

name: Shipwrecker Circus (w/ Oskar Blues)
tagline: American Barley Wine - Oskar Blues Collab.
description: In collaboration with the awesome Oskar Blues from Colorado, we created this big, twisted 10.5% American style barley wine. Big boozy aromas and a sweet viscosity, packed in with some heavy-hitting C-hops, for an intense bitterness to balance this full-bodied malt monster.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Munich, Crystal 150, Chocolate Chinook, Cascade, Citra, Chinook, Chinook, Citra, Cascade, Cascade, Chinook, Citra Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Stilton, Pan seared steak, Dark Chocolate Fondant
malts: Extra Pale, Munich, Crystal 150, Chocolate
hops: Chinook, Cascade, Citra, Chinook, Chinook, Citra, Cascade, Cascade, Chinook, Citra

name: Zephyr
description: A 9.2% Double IPA aged for 21 months in a 1965 Invergordon cask with 30 kg of fresh highland strawberries. This beer is a riot of whisky, caramel and strawberry, all tempered by a toe curling bitterness enducing rapture in all who taste it. Who needs champagne?
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150 Columbus Extract, Columbus, Columbus, Centennial, Simcoe, Columbus, Centennial, Centennial, Columbus, Simcoe, Amarillo Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Poached eggs and smoked salmon, Salt and pepper squid, Key Lime Pie
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150
hops: Columbus Extract, Columbus, Columbus, Centennial, Simcoe, Columbus, Centennial, Centennial, Columbus, Simcoe, Amarillo

name: Belgian Trappist
description: Our Unleash the Yeast series was an epic experiment into the differences in aroma and flavour provided by switching up your yeast. We brewed up a wort with a light caramel note and some toasty biscuit flavour, and hopped it with Amarillo and Centennial for a citrusy bitterness. Everything else is down to the yeast. Abbey style yeasts add distinctive spicy and fruity notes, and dry out the finished beer.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Munich Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo WLP500 - Monastery Ale
food_pairing: Roast beef with spicy jus, Ginger bread cookies, Orange tart
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Munich
hops: Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo

name: Kohatu - IPA Is Dead
description: As you’d expect from a New Zealand hop variety, Kohatu contributes bags of tropical fruit, but with loads of lime notes, & pineapple hits. Seriously fruity, with sweet, juicy melon and stonefruit notes.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal Kohatu, Kohatu, Kohatu, Kohatu Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Tuna sushi roll with spicy mayonnaise sauce, Thai green curry, Pineapple upside down cake
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal
hops: Kohatu, Kohatu, Kohatu, Kohatu

name: Hello My Name is Vladimir
tagline: Limonnik Infused Imperial IPA (Not for Gays).
description: A Limonnik-infused, triple dry- hopped double IPA. Dry berry tartness and intense citrus hop character meld with a dry bready malt base, boosted by a hint of alcohol warmth. This beer was brewed as a protest against the anti-LGBT legislation in Russia surrounding the Sochi Olympics.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Wheat Citra, Citra, Citra, Blackberry Concentrate, Sour Cherry Puree, Citra, Mosaic, Centennial Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Russian mini pork pies, Beef Stroganoff, Chocolate and fruit cake
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Wheat
hops: Citra, Citra, Citra, Blackberry Concentrate, Sour Cherry Puree, Citra, Mosaic, Centennial

name: AB:17
description: A triple whammy of coffee from HasBean gives our 17th Abstrakt concept beer an intense and roasty, dark mocha character. We brewed with espresso in the mash, cafetiere in the boil, and whole roast beans in the whirlpool and the fermenter.
ingredients: Pale Ale, Rye, Amber, Dark Crystal, Roasted Barley, Chocolate, Carafa Special Malt Type 1 CO2 Extract, Willamette Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: 12hr smoked brisket, Chocolate pistachio cakes, Dulche de leche
malts: Pale Ale, Rye, Amber, Dark Crystal, Roasted Barley, Chocolate, Carafa Special Malt Type 1
hops: CO2 Extract, Willamette

name: Hardcore IPA
tagline: Explicit Imperial Ale. Citrusy. Resinous. Intense.
description: Pounding a triple payload of the biggest North American hops humanity has devised, braced by a backbone of caramel malt, this beer is deep, astringent and resinous, pushing to the extremes of lupulin thresholds. There’s nothing inscrutable going on; no mystery in the backstory. It doesn’t seek to be understood. A beer incapable of empathy; only hop overload.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150 Columbus Extract, Columbus, Columbus, Centennial, Simcoe, Columbus, Centennial, Simcoe, Centennial, Columbus, Simcoe, Amarillo Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Spicy wings with blue cheese dip, Pan seared scallops with a chilli sauce, Creamy chocolate and caramel cheesecake
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150
hops: Columbus Extract, Columbus, Columbus, Centennial, Simcoe, Columbus, Centennial, Simcoe, Centennial, Columbus, Simcoe, Amarillo

name: American Wheat
description: A luscious blend of peach, blood orange and banana to make a suitably refreshing beverage that happily straddles the Atlantic.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Wheat, Pale Crystal Ahtanum, Ahtanum Wyeast 1010 - American Wheat™
food_pairing: Strawberry and citrus salad, Fish corn tacos with pomegranate salsa, Summer berry fruit parfait
malts: Extra Pale, Wheat, Pale Crystal
hops: Ahtanum, Ahtanum

name: Dog Wired (w/8 Wired)
description: Brewed in collaboration with Soren from New Zealand’s stellar 8-Wired brewery, this is an Imperial Pilsner featuring two of our favourite New Zealand hops: Nelson Sauvin and Motueka. Sitting at a dangerously drinkable 7.1% ABV there’s a touch of Munich malt which gives this beer that little extra caramel biscuit bite to compliment the lip smackingly tropical hops. Expect an all out NZ hoppy riot.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Munich, Acidulated Malt Nelson Sauvin, Motueka, Nelson Sauvin, Motueka, Nelson Sauvin, Motueka, Motueka, Nelson Sauvin Wyeast 2007 - Pilsen Lager™
food_pairing: Spiced and blackened cajun chicken, Pork belly vindaloo, Rhubarb pie
malts: Extra Pale, Munich, Acidulated Malt
hops: Nelson Sauvin, Motueka, Nelson Sauvin, Motueka, Nelson Sauvin, Motueka, Motueka, Nelson Sauvin

name: The Physics
description: A hoppy Amber Ale that won World's Best Amber Beer in the World Beer Awards 2007. Malt and hops are in perfect harmony in this incredibly balanced beer. Biscuity, bitter and packing a surprisingly hoppy punch, this beer ultimately morphed into 5AM Saint.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 120, Dark Crystal Amarillo, Amarillo, Bramling Cross, Amarillo Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Barbecue pulled pork on sourdough bread, Roast turkey with a honey and herb marinade and roasted vegetables, Banana walnut loaf with chocolate chips
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 120, Dark Crystal
hops: Amarillo, Amarillo, Bramling Cross, Amarillo

name: Anarchist Alchemist
description: About as far as you can push an IPA; Anarchist Alchemist packs in three times the malt and three of our favourite hops. Nelson Sauvin, Amarillo and Centennial bring a range of flavours, touching on tropical fruit, white grape, tangerine, grapefruit, pine, spiced orange... the list goes on!
ingredients: Extra Pale Nelson Sauvin, Centennial, Nelson Sauvin, Amarillo, Centennial, Nelson Sauvin, Amarillo, Centennial Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Blue cheese & onion tart, Goan goat curry, Sugar-poached kumquat rice pudding
malts: Extra Pale
hops: Nelson Sauvin, Centennial, Nelson Sauvin, Amarillo, Centennial, Nelson Sauvin, Amarillo, Centennial

name: AB:15
description: A salted caramel popcorn Imperial Ale. Bourbon and Rum barrel aged, this 12.8% ale has complex and twisting flavours. Bitter caramel, wood, smoke, spice, treacle and vanilla are all present and intertwine against a smooth and lightly chewy mouthfeel. The salted caramel popcorn lends subtle hints of a smoky brininess.
ingredients: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich, Crystal 150, Popcorn Sorachi Ace, Willamette Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Crispy bacon on flat bread, Glazed ham with crackling coating, Popcorn caramel and chocolate cake
malts: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich, Crystal 150, Popcorn
hops: Sorachi Ace, Willamette

name: Goldings - IPA Is Dead
description: This is East Kent Goldings re- invented and re-imagined and shows just what can be done with English hops if you use enough of them. In this amped up Goldings reincarnation expect to be slammed with floral lavender, a fruity riot of blackberries and spiced pears, bubblegum, plums and the illusion of thyme.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Munich Goldings, Goldings, Goldings, Goldings Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Rosemary and thyme marinated venison, Fish and chips, Lavender chocolate chip cookies
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Munich
hops: Goldings, Goldings, Goldings, Goldings

name: AB:14
description: Think banoffee pie; loads of creamy sweet banana, and sticky warm toffee. This beer is super complex, and one for the sweet-toothed!
ingredients: Wheat, Extra Pale, Munich, Caramalt Bramling Cross, Simcoe, Saaz, Simcoe, Saaz Wyeast 3638 - Bavarian Wheat™
food_pairing: Sweet pork Chinese dumplings, Caramelised onion venison burger, Banoffee pie
malts: Wheat, Extra Pale, Munich, Caramalt
hops: Bramling Cross, Simcoe, Saaz, Simcoe, Saaz

name: Lost Dog (w/Lost Abbey)
tagline: Rum-Aged Imperial Porter - Lost Abbey Collab.
description: Our first beer aged in rum casks, Lost Dog saw us brew a collaboration imperial porter with our friends at Lost Abbey. The base beer was packed with toffee, chocolate and roasty notes, balanced with a subtle spicy hop character. The rum casks add a warming, spiced vanilla edge.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Pale Chocolate, Chocolate, Dark Crystal, Flaked Oats, Caramalt First Gold Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Beef satay skewers, Venison & cranberry pie, Blackberry mocha gateaux
malts: Extra Pale, Pale Chocolate, Chocolate, Dark Crystal, Flaked Oats, Caramalt
hops: First Gold

name: TM10
description: Brewed for the Tate Modern’s 10th Anniversary. A saison style beer brewed with ginger and orange peel. Very limited batch of 4000 cork and caged bottles with a silk screened label designed by Johanna Basford. Only available at the Tate Modern.
ingredients: Pale Ale Bobek, Bobek, Bobek, Ginger, Orange Peel Wyeast 3711 - French Saison™
food_pairing: Tom yum soup, Andhra chicken pickle curry, Butterscotch tart
malts: Pale Ale
hops: Bobek, Bobek, Bobek, Ginger, Orange Peel

name: Paradox Islay
description: In 2006 James and Martin hijacked a beer dinner run by Michael Jackson, the acclaimed beer and whisky writer, and convinced him to taste one of their home brews. This was a defining moment in BrewDog prehistory, and that beer was the first incarnation of the ubiquitous Paradox. Aged in a variety of casks over the years, Paradox is dark, decadent and encapsulating. Can be enjoyed fresh; phenomenal when aged.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich, Flaked Oats, Dark Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Carafa Special Malt Type 3 Columbus, Columbus, Saaz, First Gold Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Ancho chilli beef taco, Chocolate gateaux, Rum poached pears with dark chocolate sauce
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich, Flaked Oats, Dark Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Carafa Special Malt Type 3
hops: Columbus, Columbus, Saaz, First Gold

name: Baby Dogma
description: A baby Scotch ale with dry and toasty malt flavours and hints of smoke. Toffee, biscuit and fudge abound with a spicy bitterness from the pan-global hops.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Munich, Dark Crystal, Wheat, Flaked Oats, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Amber, Weyermann Beech Smoked First Gold, Willamette, Hallertauer Mittelfrüh Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: French onion soup, Braised pheasant, Caramel sauce and hot fudge
malts: Extra Pale, Munich, Dark Crystal, Wheat, Flaked Oats, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Amber, Weyermann Beech Smoked
hops: First Gold, Willamette, Hallertauer Mittelfrüh

name: Albino Squid Assasin
description: This tentacled terminator packs a punch - ten punches to be precise. Each hop addition adds to the intense layers of depth in this red rye IPA. Toasty caramel & cinder toffee from crystal malts, cacao richness from intensely roasted malt and the spiciness of rye. Zesty pithiness from Citra and the robust resin of Chinook. This small batch exclusive brew is up-front intensity matched with twisted complexity. The can features awesome custom art from Joe Wilson.
ingredients: Pale Ale, Crystal 150, Dark Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Rye Magnum, Chinook, Citra, Chinook, Citra, Chinook, Citra Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Rocket and mozzarella salad with a cracked pepper dressing, Fried halibut with sweet potato fritters, Grapefruit and blood orange tart
malts: Pale Ale, Crystal 150, Dark Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Rye
hops: Magnum, Chinook, Citra, Chinook, Citra, Chinook, Citra

name: Amarillo - IPA Is Dead
description: Citrus fruit. Lots of citrus fruit. Think blood orange, orange zest and grapefruit, tangerine and lemon; the fruit is balanced by floral notes in the most classic of new wave IPA hops. Amarillo adds a zesty, pithy character that sits beautifully alongside hints of toffee and honeycomb.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal Amarillo, Amarillo, Amarillo, Amarillo Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Bratwurst sausage with spicy mustard, Fried American bacon with chilli flakes added to the top, Dark chocolate chip cookies
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal
hops: Amarillo, Amarillo, Amarillo, Amarillo

name: Black Eyed King Imp
description: An early Cocoa Psycho recipe that we loved, but didn't fit what we were looking for. We locked this chocolate coffee stout away in barrels for two years, imparting toasted marshmallow, spicy vanilla, molasses and boozy warmth.
ingredients: Extra Pale - Spring Blend, Wheat, Caramalt, Crystal, Dark Crystal, Amber, Brown, Chocolate, Roasted Barley Magnum, Willamette, First Gold Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Beef chilli made with cocoa powder, Dark chocolate covered bacon, Rich espresso tiramisu
malts: Extra Pale - Spring Blend, Wheat, Caramalt, Crystal, Dark Crystal, Amber, Brown, Chocolate, Roasted Barley
hops: Magnum, Willamette, First Gold

name: Prototype 27
description: Hardcore IPA with raspberries aged in Caol Ila casks. Full-bodied and compelling, the robust malt base provides an initial layer of honey, cinnamon and biscuity malt sweetness. Soon the Scottish berries are in on the act, a dominating tug of war between sweet and tart with an overbearing zest. As the beer slips back across your tongue the hops demand and definitely get your attention. At 100 IBUs the bitterness smashes into the back of your throat as the resinous, spiced orange peel flavours add depth to the berry fruitiness.
ingredients: Pale Ale, Crystal 150, Caramalt Columbus, Centennial, Columbus, Centennial, Columbus, Centennial, Simcoe Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Strong blue cheese, Cranachan, Chicago style hot links
malts: Pale Ale, Crystal 150, Caramalt
hops: Columbus, Centennial, Columbus, Centennial, Columbus, Centennial, Simcoe

name: Coffee Imperial Stout
description: This beer was released as both as "Danish Beerhouse Coffee Imperial Stout" and "BrewDog Coffee Imperial Stout". Deep, dark, roasted flavours make this a perfect Sunday brunch beer.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Dark Crystal, Chocolate, Roasted Barley Chinook, Galena, Galena, First Gold, Coffee, Coffee Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Gooey chocolate brownies, Chicken fried steak with cheesy mash, Spicy chicken empanadas
malts: Extra Pale, Dark Crystal, Chocolate, Roasted Barley
hops: Chinook, Galena, Galena, First Gold, Coffee, Coffee

name: Mandarina Bavaria - IPA Is Dead
description: From the central European plains of Germany, comes something very different. A blast of tangerine and orange, Mandarina Bavaria brings a highly distinctive backbone of flavour. This is down to its parent – Cascade – and a frankly enormous 70% myrcene oil content. If equate Germany solely with earthy, spicy Noble hops, Mandarina Bavaria will make you think again.
ingredients: Extra Pale Mandarina Bavaria, Mandarina Bavaria, Mandarina Bavaria Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Lavender and thyme roast beef, Spicy kung po chicken, Caramel and rose essence cheesecake
malts: Extra Pale
hops: Mandarina Bavaria, Mandarina Bavaria, Mandarina Bavaria

name: Dogma
tagline: Revamped Wee Heavy. Luscious. Malty. Fruity.
description: Brewed with over ten different types of malt, and blended together with Scottish heather honey, it is a pantheon to the gods of intricacy and nuance; a beer that celebratesa confluence of ideas. Complex, indulgent and encapsulating, Dogma gives more than a cursory nod to history, to make you ponder the very nature of beer itself.
ingredients: Pale Ale, Munich, Caramalt, Crystal, Dark Crystal, Wheat, Flaked Oats, Chocolate, Smoked Malt, Amber, Brown Saaz, First Gold Wyeast 2007 - Pilsen Lager™
food_pairing: Mature cheddar with red onion chutney, Honey glazed ham, Chocolate caramel drizzled sponge cake
malts: Pale Ale, Munich, Caramalt, Crystal, Dark Crystal, Wheat, Flaked Oats, Chocolate, Smoked Malt, Amber, Brown
hops: Saaz, First Gold

name: Magic Stone Dog (w/Magic Rock & Stone Brewing Co.)
tagline: Session Farmhouse IPA - Stone / Magic Rock Collab.
description: A session IPA brewed with a diverse grain bill, hopped with Simcoe and Amarillo and fermented with saison yeast, for an incredible level of depth in a low ABV beer. Spicy, fruity, complex, refreshing and dry.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Wheat, Torrified Wheat, Rye, Flaked Oats, Amber Simcoe, Amarillo Wyeast 3711 - French Saison™
food_pairing: Halibut with caper brown butter, Creamy gorgonzola and satsuma salad, Spicy Daal with garlic naan bread
malts: Extra Pale, Wheat, Torrified Wheat, Rye, Flaked Oats, Amber
hops: Simcoe, Amarillo

name: AB:08
description: Flavours and aromas you'd expect from a Stout, but brewed without dark malts. The full mouthfeel comes courtesy of wheat and oats, while smoked malt and the twist additions add the complex flavours normally provided by highly kilned malts.
ingredients: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Wheat, Flaked Oats, Smoked Peaty First Gold, First Gold, Coffee Beans Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Caramelised scallops with burnt apple puree, Blackened Cajun chicken, Blondies with chocolate fudge sauce
malts: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Wheat, Flaked Oats, Smoked Peaty
hops: First Gold, First Gold, Coffee Beans

name: Sunk Punk
description: It's rumoured just a drop can calm the fiercest of storms. A balance of sweet, salt and savoury, citrus, spruce and caramel. Fermented at the bottom of the North Sea, which just so happens to be the perfect temperature for lagers to ferment.
ingredients: Extra Pale Chinook, Ahtanum, Chinook, Ahtanum, Chinook, Ahtanum, Simcoe, Nelson Sauvin Wyeast 2007 - Pilsen Lager™
food_pairing: Salt baked cod with lemon and dill butter, Beef, oyster and ale pie, Apple and rosemary tart
malts: Extra Pale
hops: Chinook, Ahtanum, Chinook, Ahtanum, Chinook, Ahtanum, Simcoe, Nelson Sauvin

name: Sub Hop
description: Brewed for the opening of our first bar in Italy, BrewDog Firenze. A mega-hoppy Imperial Pilsner, with toasty malt complexity and tropical New World hops.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Munich, Dextrose Saaz, Hallertauer Mittelfrüh, Pacifica, Pacific Jade, Pacifica, Pacific Jade, Pacifica Wyeast 2007 - Pilsen Lager™
food_pairing: Seared lemon and herb salmon, Crab linguine, Almond biscotti
malts: Extra Pale, Munich, Dextrose
hops: Saaz, Hallertauer Mittelfrüh, Pacifica, Pacific Jade, Pacifica, Pacific Jade, Pacifica

name: Bracken's Porter
tagline: A Tribute To Our Favourite 4 Pawed Friend.
description: The beer was named Bracken’s Porter as a tribute to our favourite four pawed friend who sadly passed in 2013. Chocolately, robust, warming, laid back and lots of fun - there are plenty of similarities between the two. Bracken we miss you and we hope you like your beer. Long live the original BrewDog.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Dark Crystal, Roasted Barley, Black Malt Vic Secret, Bramling Cross, Challenger Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Grilled vegetable and chicken teriyaki skewers, Chilli covered burger (Sloppy Joe), Candied bacon topped chocolate cheesecake
malts: Extra Pale, Dark Crystal, Roasted Barley, Black Malt
hops: Vic Secret, Bramling Cross, Challenger

name: Tokyo Rising Sun - Lowland
description: A forgotten gem in the deepest, darkest corner of the warehouse. Aged in a Lowland whisky cask resulting in decadent chocolate, toasted vanilla, indulgent spiced fruit, a mesmerizingly hypnotic mouthfeel and new layers that emerge on every sip.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Dark Crystal, Chocolate, Roasted Barley Chinook, Galena, Chinook, Galena, Galena, First Gold, Chinook WLP099 - Super High Gravity Ale
food_pairing: Duck liver paté, Mutton stew, Kirsch chocolate truffles
malts: Extra Pale, Dark Crystal, Chocolate, Roasted Barley
hops: Chinook, Galena, Chinook, Galena, Galena, First Gold, Chinook

name: Hunter Foundation Pale Ale
description: This straight-up US style pale ale uses some of our favourite hops against a toasty malt base. We brewed this with Sir Tom Hunter at our Fraserburgh brewery - to add a charitable element to your own version, feel free to share this citrusy pale ale with your friends. Or don't, it's your choice.
ingredients: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Munich Amarillo, Simcoe, Amarillo, Citra Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Monterey Jack stuffed grilled jalepenos, Barbecue corn and steak fajita seasoned wrap, Cinnamon & white chocolate churro
malts: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Munich
hops: Amarillo, Simcoe, Amarillo, Citra

name: Hype
description: A perfect pale ale showcase for the tropical profile of New Zealand hops and the intense citrus of US hops.
ingredients: Maris Otter Extra Pale Nelson Sauvin, Nelson Sauvin, Amarillo Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Quince cheese, Shredded chicken and mango salsa taquitos, Poached pear
malts: Maris Otter Extra Pale
hops: Nelson Sauvin, Nelson Sauvin, Amarillo

name: AB:16
description: On the nose, clove and nutmeg, cafe au lait, subtle dark fruit notes, and hints of candied lemon peel. On the palate, smooth & fruity espresso, milk chocolate, and warm brandy-soaked currants are in the middle of a high-class dance-off against the spicy and peppery Belgian character. The overall impression evokes malt loaf or ginger cake.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Wheat, Munich, Crystal 150, Chocolate Waimea, Saaz, Fuggles Wyeast 3787 - Trappist High Gravity™
food_pairing: Roasted duck, Gorgonzola and rye nut bread with smoked honey ham, Raspberry coffee cheesecake
malts: Extra Pale, Wheat, Munich, Crystal 150, Chocolate
hops: Waimea, Saaz, Fuggles

name: Sunmaid Stout
description: Brewed by Chris Sartori from Stone Brewing Company in 2010. A dark chocolate stout with dried dark fruit finish. Simcoe provides bitterness with subtle fruity supporting notes, contrasting the chocolate and coffee-laden malt profile. The finish is warming with vanilla and rich dark fruit depth.
ingredients: Pale Ale - Tipple, Chocolate, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Crystal, Flaked Oats Simcoe, Challenger Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Lapin aux pruneaux (braised rabbit with prunes), Gouda cheese, Dark chocolate truffles
malts: Pale Ale - Tipple, Chocolate, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Crystal, Flaked Oats
hops: Simcoe, Challenger

name: Pale - Russian Doll
description: The levels of hops vary throughout the range. We love hops, so all four beers are big, bitter badasses, but by tweaking the amount of each hop used later in the boil and during dry- hopping, we can balance the malty backbone with some unexpected flavours. Simcoe is used in the whirlpool for all four beers, and yet still lends different characters to each.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal Cascade, Centennial, Citra, Simcoe, Simcoe, Cascade, Centennial, Citra Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Roast chicken with vegetables and wild rice, Fresh pico de gallo with corn tortilla, Carrot cake
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal
hops: Cascade, Centennial, Citra, Simcoe, Simcoe, Cascade, Centennial, Citra

name: Whisky Sour - B-Sides
description: Deconstructed whisky sour, reconstructed as a beer.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Acidulated Malt, Wheat Malt, Rye, Special W Amarillo, Citra, Simcoe, Amarillo, Citra, Simcoe, Amarillo, Citra, Simcoe Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Potted fresh & smoked salmon, Spiced nut loaf, Lemon poppyseed donuts
malts: Extra Pale, Acidulated Malt, Wheat Malt, Rye, Special W
hops: Amarillo, Citra, Simcoe, Amarillo, Citra, Simcoe, Amarillo, Citra, Simcoe

name: Black Eyed King Imp - Vietnamese Coffee Edition
description: This is the Vietnamese Coffee Edition. At 12.7% ABV, Black Eyed King Imp is a super intense and twistedly complex brew, with intense notes of sweet vanilla, rich espresso, smooth molasses and bitter chocolate barely contained by the whatever container it's in.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Wheat, Caramalt, Crystal, Dark Crystal, Amber, Brown, Chocolate, Roasted Barley Magnum, Willamette, First Gold Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Bacon sandwich with brown sauce, 20hr smoked brisket, Chocolate fudge ice cream
malts: Extra Pale, Wheat, Caramalt, Crystal, Dark Crystal, Amber, Brown, Chocolate, Roasted Barley
hops: Magnum, Willamette, First Gold

name: Eurotrash
description: Trashy Blonde with a Belgian Twist. Clove oil, red apples and a drier mouthfeel set this beer apart from its older sister.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich Simcoe, Amarillo, Simcoe, Amarillo, Motueka, Simcoe, Amarillo, Motueka, Simcoe, Amarillo, Motueka Wyeast 3522 - Belgian Ardennes™
food_pairing: Grilled fish salad, Angelfood cake, Pad Thai
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich
hops: Simcoe, Amarillo, Simcoe, Amarillo, Motueka, Simcoe, Amarillo, Motueka, Simcoe, Amarillo, Motueka

name: Never Mind The Anabolics
description: Never Mind the Anabolics, a 6.5% India Pale Ale brewed with copious amounts of performance-enhancing natural ingredients. Brewed to commemorate the 2012 Olympics and its merry marketing bandwagon.
ingredients: Extra Pale - Spring Blend, Wheat, Caramalt Motueka, Motueka Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Grilled chicken salad with bacon and avocado, Red pepper houmous and flat bread, Matcha green tea cake
malts: Extra Pale - Spring Blend, Wheat, Caramalt
hops: Motueka, Motueka

name: #Mashtag 2013
description: A rich, nutty Brown Ale with a deep, rich malt profile, hopped with a range of citrusy and spicy US varieties. Mellow yet endlessly complex, with enough chocolate and fruit character to balance the bitterness, and a soft oaky roundness.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Dark Crystal, Caramalt, Amber, Chocolate Motueka, Magnum, Cascade, Amarillo, Cascade, Amarillo, Willamette Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Roast beef, Roasted butternut squash, Hazelnut brittle
malts: Extra Pale, Dark Crystal, Caramalt, Amber, Chocolate
hops: Motueka, Magnum, Cascade, Amarillo, Cascade, Amarillo, Willamette

name: Hobo Pop
description: Brewed with mountains of Wheat, Rye, Cara and Crystal malts, fermented with an American ale yeast and bittered with Amarillo & Centennial, this 4.2% beer is what happens if something classy like a European wheat beer goes to live in Vegas. Zingy citrus hops and a punchy bitterness bolster this low ABV pale.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150, Wheat, Rye Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Mozzarella and tomato baked chicken, Spiced shrimp salad, Strawberry cheescake
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150, Wheat, Rye
hops: Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial

name: AB:18
tagline: Imperial Brown Ale Aged In Rum Casks.
description: AB:18 began life as an Imperial Brown Ale before we bombarded it with Scottish tayberries and Purple raspberries and locked it away in rum barrels for two years, infusing rich dark fruit flavours and oaky warmth into the mix.
ingredients: Extra Pale - Spring Blend, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Chocolate, Brown, Flaked Oats Galena, Willamette, First Gold Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Kippers and poached eggs, Slow cooked lamb shoulder with mint sauce, Apple and blackcurrant cobbler
malts: Extra Pale - Spring Blend, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Chocolate, Brown, Flaked Oats
hops: Galena, Willamette, First Gold

name: Hops Kill Nazis
description: 5AM Saint's big brother. Dry- hopping with Chinook gave Hops Kill Nazis a full-on, instantly recognisable US hop character - huge resinous aromas (think giant redwood) with a bitter grapefruit edge. The caramel malts bring flavours of toffee and burnt sugar, which gave Hops Kill Nazis a big, complex malt base supporting the intense hopping.
ingredients: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150 Chinook, Chinook, Centennial, Chinook Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Candied almond and blue cheese rocket salad, Chicken Tikka Madras, Pecan pie
malts: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150
hops: Chinook, Chinook, Centennial, Chinook

name: AB:04
tagline: Imperial Stout With Coffee, Loads Of Cocoa And Chilli.
description: Imperial Stout brewed with coffee, cocoa, Naga chillies (the hottest in the world), and champagne yeast. Possibly our most acclaimed Abstrakt yet.
ingredients: Pale Ale, Wheat Malt, Flaked Oats, Dark Crystal 350, Chocolate, Black Patent First Gold, Fuggles, Fuggles, Coffee Beans Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Beef mahaca on corn tortillas, Chilli and dark chocolate tart, Epoisses cheese
malts: Pale Ale, Wheat Malt, Flaked Oats, Dark Crystal 350, Chocolate, Black Patent
hops: First Gold, Fuggles, Fuggles, Coffee Beans

name: India Session Lager - Prototype Challenge
description: BrewDog’s level of dry-hop to a beer formed with a baseline of 100% pilsner malt – and at under 4.5% ABV – gives you a style that flirts at the edges of several others. Think aromas of fresh cut grass, nettle, white grape, melon, tangerine - with similar flavours leading to a dry, bitter finish.
ingredients: Pilsner, Dextrin Malt Chinook, Amarillo, Simcoe, Citra, Mosaic, Amarillo, Simcoe, Citra Wyeast 2007 - Pilsen Lager™
food_pairing: Tomato and rosemary palmiers, Bratwurst with sauerkraut, Lemon drizzle cake
malts: Pilsner, Dextrin Malt
hops: Chinook, Amarillo, Simcoe, Citra, Mosaic, Amarillo, Simcoe, Citra

name: Hopped-Up Brown Ale - Prototype Challenge
description: Brown ales are perfect foils for resinous C-Hops, as the piney elements of the latter contrast brilliantly with the sweeter, nutty elements of the malt bill. The best of both worlds.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Flaked Oats, Brown, Crystal 150, Munich, Carafa Special Malt Type 1 Columbus, Simcoe, Centennial, Columbus, Simcoe, Citra Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Butternut squash and sage soup, Roast beef and horseradish sandwich, Fudge
malts: Extra Pale, Flaked Oats, Brown, Crystal 150, Munich, Carafa Special Malt Type 1
hops: Columbus, Simcoe, Centennial, Columbus, Simcoe, Citra

name: Comet
description: A potently bitter hop variety originally grown in the US around 40 years ago, Comet has been newly resurrected - this German version has bold resinous grapefruit flavours, which add a huge fresh hop aroma to this IPA.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal Comet, Comet, Comet, Comet Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Margherita pizza with chili flakes, Spicy Thai peanut satay, Panna cotta with a grapefruit tuile
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal
hops: Comet, Comet, Comet, Comet

name: Baby Saison - B-Sides
description: A hark back to the origins of Saison; slight spice and earthy notes with highlights of lemon and pepper make a beer that could quench the thirst of any seasonal worker.
ingredients: Pilsner, Munich, Amber Sorachi Ace, Sorachi Ace, Mosaic, Amarillo Wyeast 3711 - French Saison™
food_pairing: Pork chop with rosemary chips, Steak tartare, Belgian waffles
malts: Pilsner, Munich, Amber
hops: Sorachi Ace, Sorachi Ace, Mosaic, Amarillo

name: Santa Paws
description: A 4.5% decadent scotch ale brewed with Scottish heather honey. A robust malty beer packed with flavour, at a strength you can drink all (Christmas) day long. Santa Paws is our antidote to the chaos of the festive season. All the flavours of Christmas pudding in liquid form.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Munich, Dark Crystal, Wheat, Flaked Oats, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Amber, Weyermann Beech Smoked First Gold, Willamette, Hallertauer Mittelfrüh Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: French onion soup, Braised pheasant, Caramel sauce and hot fudge
malts: Extra Pale, Munich, Dark Crystal, Wheat, Flaked Oats, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Amber, Weyermann Beech Smoked
hops: First Gold, Willamette, Hallertauer Mittelfrüh

name: Original Dogma (Née Speedball)
tagline: Strong Ale With Honey And Spices.
description: A strong ale, brewed with guarana, Californian poppy, kola nut and Scottish heather honey. A conspiracy of trans-continental ingredients infused with some devastatingly BrewDog imaginative thinking.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Munich, Amber, Dark Crystal Amarillo, Amarillo, Bobek, Guarana Powder, Kola Nut Powder, Poppy Seed, Heather Honey Safale US-05
food_pairing: Spicy seafood stew, French onion soup, Mexican wedding cake (cookies)
malts: Extra Pale, Munich, Amber, Dark Crystal
hops: Amarillo, Amarillo, Bobek, Guarana Powder, Kola Nut Powder, Poppy Seed, Heather Honey

name: Alpha Pop
description: A hoppy Rye Ale loaded with an avalanche of citrus and resinous flavours. Columbus, our high-alpha friend, lends a huge pithy citrus blast, with Ahtanum providing a punchy tropical fruit back-up. Brewing with rye adds a spiciness to the speciality malt caramel backbone, giving a warm ginger snap flavour, before slowly the hops, barley and rye combine and build to an orangey, biscuity, almost chocolatey crescendo.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Rye Columbus, Columbus, Ahtanum, Ahtanum, Ahtanum, Columbus Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Spicy lamb tikka masala, Spicy beef and Mexican black bean burger, Poached cinnamon apple muffins
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Rye
hops: Columbus, Columbus, Ahtanum, Ahtanum, Ahtanum, Columbus

name: Bavarian Weizen
description: Our Unleash the Yeast series was an epic experiment into the differences in aroma and flavour provided by switching up your yeast. We brewed up a wort with a light caramel note and some toasty biscuit flavour, and hopped it with Amarillo and Centennial for a citrusy bitterness. Everything else is down to the yeast. Bavarian Weizen yeast adds traditional weissbier notes of banana and clove.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Munich Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo WLP351 - Bavarian Weizen
food_pairing: Spicy paella, German bratwurst with spicy mustard dip and vinaigrette salad, Creamy eggs benedict
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Munich
hops: Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo

name: Citra
description: The Pacific North West of America is home to the Citra hop. America is not just about cheer leaders, a silly version of football, elastic top jeans and cheeseburgers. They grow remarkable hops and Citra is a killer example of this, embodying all that is good about American hops and then some. Fearfully hard to resist, this beer is loaded with brash citrus, grapefruit, orange, hints of resinous pine and touches of blackcurrant. Devilishly moreish.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Crystal 150, Caramalt Citra, Citra, Citra Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Lemon and herb salmon, Sharp cheddar with mango chutney, Shredded chicken tacos with pico de gallo
malts: Extra Pale, Crystal 150, Caramalt
hops: Citra, Citra, Citra

name: #Mashtag 2015
description: Democratically voted on by you and the BrewDog beer community. A wonderfully burnt toast malt backbone, loaded with American Hops for floral, citrus flavours and warm boozy vanilla and toasted oak.
ingredients: Pale Ale, Munich, Caramalt, Special W, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Carafa Special Malt Type 3 Nugget, Columbus, Centennial, Simcoe, Centennial, Simcoe, Willamette, Centennial, Simcoe, Willamette Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Charcuterie platter (featuring Italian salami), Blue cheese wedge salad, Rich dark chocolate volcano cake
malts: Pale Ale, Munich, Caramalt, Special W, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Carafa Special Malt Type 3
hops: Nugget, Columbus, Centennial, Simcoe, Centennial, Simcoe, Willamette, Centennial, Simcoe, Willamette

name: Dead Pony Club
tagline: West Coast Kicks. Citrusy. Zesty. Bright.
description: Our California style West Coast IPA has light toffee and caramel notes layered on biscuit malt, supporting a huge, fresh citrus aroma, with lemongrass, lime zest, grapefruit peel, alongside some tropical notes, courtesy of some heavy-hitting US hops.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150 Simcoe, Citra, Simcoe, Citra, Simcoe, Citra, Mosaic Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Baja style fish tacos, Jerk chicken, Apple crumble
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150
hops: Simcoe, Citra, Simcoe, Citra, Simcoe, Citra, Mosaic

name: AB:09
description: This Cranachan Imperial Stout was inspired by the famous Scottish dessert, and brewed with a mountain of dark malts, loads of oats, Scottish heather honey and local raspberries. The beer was then transferred to oak casks to mature for 6 months.
ingredients: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Flaked Oats, Crystal 150, Dark Crystal 350-400 Fuggles, Fuggles Champagne
food_pairing: Aged cheddar with honey and raspberry chutney, Rich beef stew with winter vegetables and a dash of honey, Scottish raspberry cranachan parfait
malts: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Flaked Oats, Crystal 150, Dark Crystal 350-400
hops: Fuggles, Fuggles

name: Mango Gose - B-Sides
description: Kettle soured hoppy mango gose. A delicate balance of sweet, juicy mango, sour lime and salinity.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Wheat Malt, Dark Crystal Sorachi Ace, Amarillo, Sorachi Ace, Amarillo Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Okra fries, Sea bass ceviche, Sea salt fudge
malts: Extra Pale, Wheat Malt, Dark Crystal
hops: Sorachi Ace, Amarillo, Sorachi Ace, Amarillo

name: Everday Anarchy
tagline: White Wine Barrel-Aged Imperial Red Saison.
description: This French white wine barrel aged Imperial Saison has a plethora of intertwining flavours. Huge aromas of peach, syrup, tangerine, sherry, toffee and raisin, followed by a dynamic bracing acidity.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Wheat, Rye Motueka, Saaz, Bobek, Saaz, Bobek Wyeast 3711 - French Saison™
food_pairing: Spiced carrot and coriander soup, Spicy chilli king prawns, Orange zest tart
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Wheat, Rye
hops: Motueka, Saaz, Bobek, Saaz, Bobek

name: Peroxide Punk
description: A trashy blonde concession for those who felt that our original 6% Punk IPA recipe was too hard hitting. This was also the first time we experimented with dry hopping our beers, giving Peroxide Punk a depth of flavour that belies its modest ABV. Zesty, aromatic and thirst quenching.
ingredients: Maris Otter Amarillo, Simcoe, Amarillo, Crystal, Liberty, Simcoe, Amarillo Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Sashimi, Pan roasted poussin with spring veg, Lemon and thyme panna cotta
malts: Maris Otter
hops: Amarillo, Simcoe, Amarillo, Crystal, Liberty, Simcoe, Amarillo

name: Lumberjack Stout
description: Lumberjack Stout is an intense beast that took its inspriation from what an actual bona-fide lumberjack might have for breakfast. Flavours of molasses, chocolate, smoke, berry, coffee and more, with a low bitterness, leaning this beer firmly towards the malty side.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Flaked Oats, Smoked Malt, Crystal Galena, Willamette Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Maple syrup drizzled chocolate chip pancakes, Fried bacon with crispy honeycomb bits, Coffee cake
malts: Extra Pale, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Flaked Oats, Smoked Malt, Crystal
hops: Galena, Willamette

name: Bowman's Beard - B-Sides
description: Ice-distilled double barley wine brewed by Chris from Stone Brewing Co. (see Sunmaid Stout) and BrewDog's own brewers. As robust, resinous and badass as its eponymic beard.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Rye, CaraAroma, Caramunich, Brown, Caramalt, Crystal, Munich Motueka, First Gold, Galena, Motueka, First Gold, Galena Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™ & Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Celery and stilton soup, Salted caramel soufflé
malts: Extra Pale, Rye, CaraAroma, Caramunich, Brown, Caramalt, Crystal, Munich
hops: Motueka, First Gold, Galena, Motueka, First Gold, Galena
yeast: Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™ & Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™

name: Pumpkin King
description: We're turning Hallowe’en inside out and upside down. Pumpkin King is not your usual unctuous, cloyingly sweet Hallowe’en pumpkin ale. Sure, there’s a huge heady hit of pungent spice on the nose, but it’s followed with bright and zesty citrus flavours, and a light mouthfeel. Spicy and sweet autumnal favourites like toasted marshmallow and toffee apple are just some of the complex notes you’ll find in our twisted take on a pumpkin ale, which weighs in at 5.4% ABV.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Munich, Dark Crystal, Amber Magnum, Willamette, First Gold Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Creamy maple syrup and bacon soup, Chunky chicken and vegetable spiced stew, Pumpkin pie
malts: Extra Pale, Munich, Dark Crystal, Amber
hops: Magnum, Willamette, First Gold

name: Hello My Name Is Päivi
description: Brewed with sea buckthorn, a tart and bitter berry found on the Finnish coastline. Bright, vibrant aromas of tangerine, mandarin and peach, with zesty hits of lime, envelop the nutty, caramel malt backbone. The intense fruitiness gives a jammy quality to the nose. On the palate is a warm biscuity sweetness, with tropical fruits in a supporting role to a huge grapefruit and orange bitterness.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt Challenger, Bravo, Comet, EXP 366, Centennial, Simcoe, Citra, Comet, Centennial, Simcoe, Citra Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Korvapuusti (cinnamon and cardamom buns), Spicy orange chicken marmalade served with potato bread, Sea buckthorn cheesecake
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt
hops: Challenger, Bravo, Comet, EXP 366, Centennial, Simcoe, Citra, Comet, Centennial, Simcoe, Citra

name: Elvis Juice V2.0 - Prototype Challenge
description: Punchy resinous hoppy aromas blast from the glass; light floral and citrus notes riff against huge piney character. Showcasing Citra, Simcoe and Amarillo at their absolute best. A huge dose of grapefruit peel brings swirls of fresh pithy zest, accentuating the dry hops and building on the dry, biscuit malt base.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt Magnum, Simcoe, Amarillo, Mosaic, Citra, Amarillo, Simcoe, Citra, Amarillo, Simcoe Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Mexican ceviche, Coriander and lime green thai curry, Grapefruit souffle
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt
hops: Magnum, Simcoe, Amarillo, Mosaic, Citra, Amarillo, Simcoe, Citra, Amarillo, Simcoe

name: Riptide
description: The original BrewDog, Bracken decided to make a beer that best reflected himself; this is the beer equivalent of the big, cute chocolate monster. Soft, smooth, dark, chocolatey and a force to be reckoned with. This gentle giant will never bite, but you'll still want to be on your best behaviour!
ingredients: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Dark Crystal 350-400, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Caramalt, Chocolate, Wheat, Flaked Oats Columbus, Galena, Galena, Cascade, Columbus Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Seared scallops, Pan seared venison with fruit salad side, Caramelised apple pie with vanilla ice cream
malts: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Dark Crystal 350-400, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Caramalt, Chocolate, Wheat, Flaked Oats
hops: Columbus, Galena, Galena, Cascade, Columbus

name: Peach Therapy
description: 9% abv sour tripel, infused with peach and apricot in collaboration with some of our favourite beer writers Adrian Tierney-Jones, Matt Curtis and Jonny and Brad from The Craft Beer Channel.
ingredients: Extra Pale Mandarina Bavaria, Strisselspalt, Mandarina Bavaria, Strisselspalt Wyeast 3522 - Belgian Ardennes™
food_pairing: Summer salad with pickled veg, Sticky barbecue spare ribs, Blueberry and almond tart
malts: Extra Pale
hops: Mandarina Bavaria, Strisselspalt, Mandarina Bavaria, Strisselspalt

name: Clown King
description: A heavy hitting combination of rich malt flavours and relentless, bitter hops. Aromas of caramel and toasted marshmallow, with raisin and dried fruit, alongside a spicy undercurrent of resin. With toasty malt and sweet dark fruit flavours, and a smooth, chewy mouthfeel, you’ll be lulled into a false sense of security, before the intense pine-sap resin draws out a huge bitter finish.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150, Brown, Munich Magnum, Simcoe, Mosaic, Ahtanum, Ahtanum, Mosaic, Mosaic, Ahtanum, Simcoe Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Aged Stilton, Flaky pastry beef pie and sweet potato mash, Chocolate pecan praline cake
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150, Brown, Munich
hops: Magnum, Simcoe, Mosaic, Ahtanum, Ahtanum, Mosaic, Mosaic, Ahtanum, Simcoe

name: India Pale Weizen (w/ Weihenstephan)
description: BrewDog vs. Weihenstephan India Pale Weizen kicked off a new direction for our collaborations. We took a simple concept (by our standards) and teamed up with the oldest brewery in the world to brew a mash-up beer using the signature styles of both breweries. India Pale Weizen has classic base hefeweizen aromas and flavours of banana, clove and bubblegum, with a distinctive haziness. Layered on top of this is a tapestry of US citrus hop character. India Pale Weizen is a perfect symbiosis of traditional and modern brewing.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Wheat, Dark Crystal Cascade, Cascade, Saaz, Hersbrucker Wyeast 3638 - Bavarian Wheat™
food_pairing: Korean barbecue nachos, Beef pho soup, Waffles with caramelised apple and powdered sugar
malts: Extra Pale, Wheat, Dark Crystal
hops: Cascade, Cascade, Saaz, Hersbrucker

name: Hello My Name Is Beastie
description: A Scottish take on Hello My Name is Ingrid with added brambles. Caramel malt provides sweetness to balance the tart berry character, which loses sweetness during fermentation.
ingredients: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt Columbus, Centennial, Columbus, Centennial, Nelson Sauvin, Bramling Cross/ First Gold, Columbus, Centennial, Nelson Sauvin Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Honey glazed ham with pineapple, Spicy wings with blue cheese sauce, Blackberry pie with vanilla ice cream
malts: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt
hops: Columbus, Centennial, Columbus, Centennial, Nelson Sauvin, Bramling Cross/ First Gold, Columbus, Centennial, Nelson Sauvin

name: Punk IPA 2010 - Current
tagline: Post Modern Classic. Spiky. Tropical. Hoppy.
description: Punk IPA. Amplified. In 2010 we finally got our paws on the equipment we needed to dry hop our beers. We focused all our energy on dry hopping, amping up the aroma and flavour of our flagship beer to create a relentless explosion of tropical fruits, and adding a hint of Caramalt to balance out the insane amount of hops.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt Chinook, Ahtanum, Chinook, Ahtanum, Chinook, Ahtanum, Simcoe, Nelson Sauvin, Chinook, Ahtanum, Simcoe, Nelson Sauvin, Cascade, Amarillo Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Spicy carne asada with a pico de gallo sauce, Shredded chicken tacos with a mango chilli lime salsa, Cheesecake with a passion fruit swirl sauce
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt
hops: Chinook, Ahtanum, Chinook, Ahtanum, Chinook, Ahtanum, Simcoe, Nelson Sauvin, Chinook, Ahtanum, Simcoe, Nelson Sauvin, Cascade, Amarillo

name: HBC 366 - IPA Is Dead
description: A new, at-the-time un-named American hop now known as Equinox. Piney, resinous with spicy fruit notes and biting grapefruit. Stewed orange and pineapple with a resinous edge.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal HBC 366, HBC 366, HBC 366, HBC 366 Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Spicy black bean and chicken tortilla soup, Spicy lamb tikka masala, Fruity bread pudding
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal
hops: HBC 366, HBC 366, HBC 366, HBC 366

name: American Ale
description: Our Unleash the Yeast series was an epic experiment into the differences in aroma and flavour provided by switching up your yeast. We brewed up a wort with a light caramel note and some toasty biscuit flavour, and hopped it with Amarillo and Centennial for a citrusy bitterness. Everything else is down to the yeast. American Ale used a clean fermenting strain which provides some faint fruity notes.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Munich Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Fried brie bites, American cheese burger, Poached apple tart
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Munich
hops: Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo

name: Cocoa Psycho
tagline: Russian Imperial Stout. Rich. Decadent. Mocha.
description: Vanilla pods and toasted oak chips add a rounded character to this massive Russian Imperial Stout, brewed with a hefty malt bill, cacao nibs and coffee beans. Dark malts combine with Cascade to add a punchy bitterness, strong enough to offset the big chocolate sweetness.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Wheat, Dark Crystal, Black Malt, Roasted Barley, Weyermann Smoked Cascade, Cascade Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Smokey sweet pulled brisket, Espresso crusted venison with a dark cherry jus, Affogato with vanilla ice cream
malts: Extra Pale, Wheat, Dark Crystal, Black Malt, Roasted Barley, Weyermann Smoked
hops: Cascade, Cascade

name: Truffle and Chocolate Stout - B-Sides
description: Pilot Brew - Truffle & Chocolate Stout. Deep, earthy roast notes make this a gastronome's dream.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Special W, Roasted Barley, Dark Crystal Sorachi Ace, Sorachi Ace, Sorachi Ace, Sorachi Ace Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Mushroom pithivier, Roast pheasant with savoy cabbage, Dark chocolate ganache macaroons
malts: Extra Pale, Special W, Roasted Barley, Dark Crystal
hops: Sorachi Ace, Sorachi Ace, Sorachi Ace, Sorachi Ace

name: Vagabond Pilsner
description: Take the thirst-quenching crispness of a German Pilsner and combine it with lemon and honey to produce a rewarding modern twist on a beer classic.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Munich, Crystal 150, Acidulated Malt Cascade, Amarillo, Centennial, Chinook, Cascade, Centennial, Chinook, Amarillo Wyeast 2007 - Pilsen Lager™
food_pairing: Jamaican jerk chicken, Hot dog with grilled onions and spicy ketchup, Shortbread and raspberry jam thumbprint cookie
malts: Extra Pale, Munich, Crystal 150, Acidulated Malt
hops: Cascade, Amarillo, Centennial, Chinook, Cascade, Centennial, Chinook, Amarillo

name: Vote Sepp
description: Vote Sepp is a single hop wheat beer brewed to a session strength, with hibiscus flower, which gives it an impressively vibrant shade of pink. What Vote Sepp lacks in complexity, it more than makes up for in a perfect balance of tartness, bitterness and body.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Torrified Wheat Motueka, Motueka, Motueka Wyeast 3944 - Belgian Witbier™
food_pairing: Crab roll sushi with strawberries, Artichoke hearts and chicken melt, Caprese salad (mozzarella, tomato, basil, black pepper and sea salt)
malts: Extra Pale, Torrified Wheat
hops: Motueka, Motueka, Motueka

name: Hello My Name Is Ingrid
description: A Double IPA with cloudberries added to the conditioning tank. One thing is certain – this Swedish inspired Double IPA is not as innocent as she first appears. A seductive body of rich malts and a buxom amount of Citra, Nelson Sauvin and Bramling Cross hops have been added to fresh Scandinavian cloudberries to deliver this beer’s tart finish.
ingredients: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt Columbus, Centennial, Columbus, Centennial, Nelson Sauvin, Bramling Cross/ First Gold, NZ Nelson Sauvin, Bramling Cross, Simcoe Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Crayfish with a chilli, coriander infused butter dip, Smörgås with cream topping, Cardamom cake with powder sugar and cloudberry jam
malts: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt
hops: Columbus, Centennial, Columbus, Centennial, Nelson Sauvin, Bramling Cross/ First Gold, NZ Nelson Sauvin, Bramling Cross, Simcoe

name: U-Boat (w/ Victory Brewing)
tagline: Smoked Porter Collab With Victory Brewing.
description: On the palate is a big dark malt sweetness, balanced by the blend of spicy Mittelfruh and citrussy Galena. Cocoa powder, rich dark chocolate, and ripe berries interplay with a toasty burnt sugar bitterness. The mouthfeel is thick and chewy with a treacly quality that doesn’t cloy, as it plays off against the hops and roast malt bitterness.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Crystal 150, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Chocolate, Munich, Smoked Warminster Hallertauer Mittelfrüh, Hallertauer Mittelfrüh, Galena Wyeast 2007 - Pilsen Lager™
food_pairing: Smoked bratwurst and mustard, Chargrilled steak, Grilled pineapple
malts: Extra Pale, Crystal 150, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Chocolate, Munich, Smoked Warminster
hops: Hallertauer Mittelfrüh, Hallertauer Mittelfrüh, Galena

name: Melon And Cucumber IPA - B-Sides
description: A Pilot Brew with 200Kg of fresh melon and 5Kg fresh cucumber added after fermentation to produce the perfect summer refreshment.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt Ahtanum, Chinook, Ahtanum, Chinook, Ahtanum, Simcoe, Nelson Sauvin Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Beef carpaccio, Chilled beetroot soup, Korean watermelon salad
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt
hops: Ahtanum, Chinook, Ahtanum, Chinook, Ahtanum, Simcoe, Nelson Sauvin

name: Morag's Mojito - B-Sides
description: A cunning cocktail blend of grapefruit hops, ginger spice and refreshing mint.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Ginger Root Citra, Citra, Citra Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Tamale, Salt cod croquettes, Mint cheesecake
malts: Extra Pale, Ginger Root
hops: Citra, Citra, Citra

name: Hop Rocker
description: The first of our foray into lager beer, Hop Rocker is a high impact, hoppy behemoth made with 100% malt. Since 2007 we have been obsessive about quality, using only the best ingredients to ensure the flavour and craftsmanship of the beer in your glass. Hop Rocker is testament to that. The malt base gives this beer a sweet, balanced complexity while the combination of New Zealand and German hops merges new world tropical juiciness with old world peppery spice.
ingredients: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich Cascade, Saaz, Cascade, Motueka, Chinook Saflager S189
food_pairing: Cajun spiced chicken wings, Mild cheddar, Lemon tart
malts: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich
hops: Cascade, Saaz, Cascade, Motueka, Chinook

name: Bounty Hunter - Shareholder Brew
description: Brewed with our Equity Punks this rich, smooth stout is brewed with a blend of six malts, resulting in a welcoming, resonant black beer. From start to finish it carries an intense roastiness reminiscent of dark chocolate intertwined with a delicate hint of coconut and caramel.
ingredients: Pale Ale, Amber, Flaked Oats, Chocolate, Roasted Barley, Carafa Special Malt Type 3 Galena Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Coconut beef red curry, Butternut squash soup with toasted almonds, Chocolate coated macaroons
malts: Pale Ale, Amber, Flaked Oats, Chocolate, Roasted Barley, Carafa Special Malt Type 3
hops: Galena

name: Zeitgeist
