description: Zeitgeist is an idiosyncratic alternative black lager. Its inspiration is found more than 200 years ago. Zeitgeist takes an age old classic, a forgotten masterpiece, and gives it relevance and an avant-garde edge.
ingredients: Organic Lager, Organic Caramalt, Organic Munich, Organic Chocolate Cascade, Cascade Saflager S189
food_pairing: Spicy cajun fried chicken, Pork dumplings with rich soy sauce, Cinnamon carrot cake with creamy cheese frosting
malts: Organic Lager, Organic Caramalt, Organic Munich, Organic Chocolate
hops: Cascade, Cascade

name: AB:10
tagline: Imperial Brown Ale Aged In Spanish Red Wine Barrels.
description: A decadent, robust and encapsulating Imperial Ale. A rollercoaster of devilish berries, smooth vanilla, toasted marshmallow and wine gums; caramel malt balanced with moderate bitterness and a roasty edge.
ingredients: Extra Pale - Spring Blend, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Chocolate, Brown, Flaked Oats Galena, Willamette, First Gold Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Calves' liver with onion relish, Coq au vin, S'mores
malts: Extra Pale - Spring Blend, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Chocolate, Brown, Flaked Oats
hops: Galena, Willamette, First Gold

name: Punk Monk
description: Old world meets new in this trans-atlantic mash up of brewing ingredients. Belgian funk incorporates itself into the pithy, resin and grapefruit, with pineapple and banana rounding out a rambunctious avalanche of fruity hops.
ingredients: Extra Pale Ahtanum, Chinook, Crystal, Chinook, Ahtanum, Chinook, Motueka, Chinook Wyeast 3522 - Belgian Ardennes™
food_pairing: Moules frites, Thai green curry, Lemon posset
malts: Extra Pale
hops: Ahtanum, Chinook, Crystal, Chinook, Ahtanum, Chinook, Motueka, Chinook

name: Dog Fight (w/ Flying Dog)
description: A clash of kings. A spiced toffee malt backbone arranged against a tidal wave of US hops. Citrus, nectarine and juicy tropical fruits are layered into this complex beer.
ingredients: Extra Pale - Spring Blend, Caramalt, Rye Chinook, Amarillo, Chinook, Amarillo, Chinook Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Black bean and avocado enchiladas with mole sauce, Mexican spiced cheddar cheese, Pancakes with maple syrup
malts: Extra Pale - Spring Blend, Caramalt, Rye
hops: Chinook, Amarillo, Chinook, Amarillo, Chinook

name: Candy Kaiser
description: In this northern German style retro altbier, we’ve dialled down the dry-hops to zero, but cranked up the malt to create massive aromas. Toasty, toffee and floral notes duke it out for supremacy in the headspace of your glass. When this all hits your palate, the steely bitterness combines with the rich dry malt and the subtle alcohol warmth in a full throttle attack on your taste buds.
ingredients: Pale Ale, Munich, Carafa Special Malt Type 1 Magnum, Hersbrucker Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Aged gouda, German bratwurst sausage, Poached pear fritters
malts: Pale Ale, Munich, Carafa Special Malt Type 1
hops: Magnum, Hersbrucker

name: Chaos Theory
description: Chaos Theory is the most under- rated achievement of 20th Century science. This beer can only aspire to parallel to the mathematical use of the word chaos, which is at odds to the common parlance. The purest showcase of the magnificent hop that is Nelson Sauvin; grapefruit, pineapple and caramel sing above the chaos of life.
ingredients: Pale Ale, Caramalt, Crystal 150 Nelson Sauvin, Nelson Sauvin, Nelson Sauvin, Nelson Sauvin Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Spicy mexican meatball stew, Habenero and mango pulled pork tacos, Spiced pumpkin pie with chocolate whipped cream
malts: Pale Ale, Caramalt, Crystal 150
hops: Nelson Sauvin, Nelson Sauvin, Nelson Sauvin, Nelson Sauvin

name: Juniper Wheat Beer
tagline: American Style Wheat Ale With Juniper Berries.
description: A variant on the 2008 release of Bad Pixie, but hoppier. Substituting the lemon peel for Ahtanum provided a vibrant floral and lemon citrus hit, balancing the slight tartness from the wheat. This dry, effervescent brew is perfect on Scotland's one day of summer.
ingredients: Pale Ale, Wheat Ahtanum, Ahtanum, Juniper Berries Wyeast 1010 - American Wheat™
food_pairing: Herring rollmops, Chicken schnitzel, Gin & elderflower jelly
malts: Pale Ale, Wheat
hops: Ahtanum, Ahtanum, Juniper Berries

name: Jet Black Heart
tagline: Oatmeal Milk Stout. Dark. Roasty. Velvety.
description: Good things come to those who wait. This smooth and roasty oatmeal milk stout won our 2015 Prototype Challenge at a canter. Roasty coffee and chocolate lead to a decadent, full-bodied richness of near uncharted depths with a velvet mouthfeel from the addition of oatmeal and a touch of wheat. This is complemented at every turn by the Magnum and Sorachi Ace hops, with the latter bringing an intensity of smooth vanilla and dark berry fruit on the long, rewarding finish.
ingredients: Pale Ale, Wheat, Dark Crystal, Brown, Black Malt, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Flaked Oats, Crystal 150, Lactose Magnum, Sorachi Ace Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Oyster beignets, Beef shin stew, A Shakin' jesse
malts: Pale Ale, Wheat, Dark Crystal, Brown, Black Malt, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Flaked Oats, Crystal 150, Lactose
hops: Magnum, Sorachi Ace

name: Galaxy

name: Hinterland
description: Hinterland is a beer long in the creation, and even longer in the appreciation. On the aroma, deep reverberating roasty bitterness and sweet dark chocolate. Also in evidence, woodsmoke, rich vanilla, mocha and marzipan. When tasting, Hinterland reveals itself as the beer moves from cellar temperature to something warmer, yielding all of the above plus dried fruit, rich ganache and ending on a resoundingly warming finish redolent of chocolate liqueur or plum brandy.

description: Out of order and stability comes the rush of the pack. Berry and caramel riding alongside marmalade and chocolate. Spice and toast jostle with lychee and biscuit. The needle flicks to all points of the compass. It drives you towards the horizon, towards the vanishing point. And it keeps going...

name: Mr.Miyagi's Wasabi Stout
tagline: Spicy Stout Brewed By Aberdeen Bar Staff.

description: This is IPA amplified, the most evocative style of the craft beer resistance with the volume cranked off the scale. Kettle hopped, dry hopped then freeze hopped for a deep fruit, resinous and spicy aroma. A full on attack on your taste buds ensues as the incredibly smooth liquid delivers a crescendo of malt, sweet honey, hop oils and a torpedo of hop bitterness that lasts and lasts.

name: Dog A
tagline: Cacao, Coffee, Chili Imperial Anniversary Stout.
description: Our anniversary stout was based on AB:04, one of our most sought after beers ever. This beer is slightly different each year, with subtle variations coming into play purely down to environmental and fermentation factors. What doesn't change is the rich dark chocolate, bitter coffee and chili warmth of this monumental stout.

name: Born To Die
description: Savagely bitter, exceptionally dry, this IPA is born to die on a predetermined day. It proudly displays its short-lived life span front and centre. There is no better time to drink this than the moment you get your paws on it. Awesome bitterness backed up by unrelenting aromas of resin, citrus, and juicy fruit. Born To Die is a eulogy to the hops that sacrificed themselves in its creation. An incredibly ambitious and satisfying small batch brew.

description: Our most involved beer, Tokyo* is an Imperial Stout brewed with copious amounts of specialty malts, jasmine and cranberries, dry-hopped with a bucket-load of our favourite hops and then carefully aged on toasted French oak chips. It’s all about moderation. Everything in moderation, including moderation itself...

description: Nelson is a love it or hate it kinda hop. We are cool with that, if we wanted to keep everyone happy we would be brewing Fosters anyway. Sharp as a razor, this New Zealand hop slices its way through your taste buds and is brutally resinous, almost scraping the intense flavours of passion fruit along your poor tongue. There is a huge depth of tropical fruit flavour with astringent gooseberry balanced against the robust malt base. Throw another shrimp on the barbie mate and you are all set. New Zealand is near Austria, right?
ingredients: Extra Pale, Crystal 150, Caramalt Nelson Sauvin, Nelson Sauvin Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™

hops: Nelson Sauvin, Nelson Sauvin

description: This beer hits all the high-points of Hello My Name is Ingrid – with one important exception. Brewed at 4.4% abv, Little Ingrid is a session- strength version of our cloudberry- infused celebration of all that is epic about Sweden. The zesty balance of citrus from the four different hops is just as pronounced as in the original.

name: No Label
description: No Label is a postmodern, postgender non-binary brew; the world’s first beer made with transgender hops. Brewed with whole hop bines that have spontaneously changed from female to male, no label goes its own way. No Label balances a light, biscuity dryness from the malt base with delicate hints of fruity esters gifted by the fermentation. Finally, dry- hopping adds a layer of new world tropical & pine flavours that add a unique twist to this classic Kölsch style beer. All profits from the sales of this beer were donated to LGBTQI+ events organisers Queerest of the Queer.
ingredients: Pilsner, Wheat, Munich Mosaic, Cascade, Jester, Cascade, Mosaic Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™

description: This Old World Stout perfectly recreates the export stouts of years gone by; brewed to imperial strength to avoid freezing during its journey across the Baltic Sea to snowy Moscow. Full bodied with huge chocolate, coffee and roast flavours, this imperial stout employs a variety of hops to add enough bitterness and hop complexity to balance the huge malt sweetness and rich mocha and molasses flavours.

Small caramel malt additions provide a touch of malt complexity. Simcoe, arguably our favourite hop, carries this beer - pine, tropical fruit and bitterness are its specialities.

description: Punk multiplied by Jack Hammer, divided by passionfruit with some Brazilian spirit factored in too. A well-rounded IPA, with bags of tropical flavour boosted by the addition of passionfruit, which unsurprisingly dominates the aroma of this summery IPA.

name: Restorative Beverage For Invalids And Convalescents
tagline: An Extract Taken From "A Treatise on Food and Diet" By Dr Jonathan Pereira, 1843.
description: Brewed to 8.5%, light as a mass market Pilsner in colour, fermented to be as dry as a Lambic, but as bitter as any double IPA and loaded with as much hop aroma as we can get into a beer. The fermentables in this beer were Maris Otter Extra Pale along with plenty of sugar as we mashed at a very low temperature to ensure maximum fermentability and attenuation. This beer is fermented within an inch of its life making it dry, sheer and bright. Citra, Amarillo & Centennial were all used in abundance in the kettle and also fired extremely liberally at this beer with our high tech hop cannon.
ingredients: Maris Otter Extra Pale, White Cane Sugar C02 Extract, Citra, Amarillo, Centennial, Citra, Amarillo, Centennial Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Habanero spicy chicken wings with ranch sauce, Jalapeño chilli and chicken quesadillas, New York style cheesecake
malts: Maris Otter Extra Pale, White Cane Sugar
hops: C02 Extract, Citra, Amarillo, Centennial, Citra, Amarillo, Centennial

name: Tokyo Rising Sun - Highland
description: A forgotten gem in the deepest, darkest corner of the warehouse. Aged in a Highland whisky cask resulting in a viscous slow motion roller coaster of powdered cacao, hints of burning pirate ships, salted caramel, sharp berries and toasted marshmallow.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Dark Crystal, Chocolate, Roasted Barley Chinook, Galena, Chinook, Galena, Galena, First Gold, Chinook WLP099 - Super High Gravity Ale

malts: Extra Pale, Dark Crystal, Chocolate, Roasted Barley

name: 77 Lager
description: Think of everything you know about lagers. Then forget it all instantly. 77 will redefine the experience forever. A Lager that actually tastes of something? You have to be kidding, right? 77 lager is made with 100% malt and whole leaf hops. It contains no preservatives, additives, cheap substitutes or any other junk. Maybe we are crazy. So what? Taste 77 Lager and we are pretty sure you will agree that the fine line between genius and insanity has just become a little more blurred.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich Hallertauer Mittelfrüh, Hallertauer Mittelfrüh, Tettnang, Saaz Wyeast 2007 - Pilsen Lager™
food_pairing: Aromatic spicy red thai curry, Sticky spicy barbecue ribs with a strong blue cheese dipping sauce, Creamy warm baked goats cheese salad
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich
hops: Hallertauer Mittelfrüh, Hallertauer Mittelfrüh, Tettnang, Saaz

name: This. Is. Lager
description: Brewed with 100% malt, ten times the hops of most industrial lagers and cold-conditioned for five weeks, this spicy, robust Pilsner is lager reborn. Expect a robust, full-bodied malt character on the front of the tongue, spicy citrus notes as it goes back through the palate and an assertive bitter finish with a lemon and pepper character to round things off.

food_pairing: Mexican ceviche, Blue cheese crumbled over wedges, Gooey lemon bar
malts: Pilsner
hops: Columbus, Hersbrucker, Saaz

name: Ella - IPA Is Dead
description: 2015 IPA is Dead Series. Supremely floral, this hugely under-rated hop is related to Galaxy and was first cultivated in the Australian state of Victoria. Initially given the same name as a certain Eurolager, their lawyers got involved and the St- prefix was dropped. Ella displays subtle notes of spice, but is fundamentally a truly floral bouquet, redolent of the Southern Hemisphere.

name: Barley Wine - Russian Doll
description: Russian Doll was an experimental set of brews showcasing the effects of varying the amount and ratio of malts in the grist. The barley wine had rich, chewy dark fruit aromas balanced with a spike of zesty hops. Toffee, apricot jam and grapefruit pith, crammed into the head of our little Russian Doll family.

description: A foundation of caramel malt is buttressed by a raucously resinous bitterness, as the rioting backdrop of citrus and tropical fruit flow in waves from those twin titans of the US – Centennial and Amarillo. And it also happens to be gluten free.

hops: Centennial, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo, Amarillo, Centennial, Amarillo

tagline: The New Black. Roasty. Hoppy. Fruity.
description: A dark hop bomb combining the malt-forward indulgences of a stout with the insatiable hopload of an IPA. Rich spiced blackcurrant and caramel up front, with a sharp bitter finish following behind, bringing grapefruit and resin with it. Dry, bitter and intense; this is an IPA first and foremost, given a dark malt makeover. Originally brewed as a Simcoe only single hop IPA, we've experimented with adding a little Cascade and Mosaic for extra depth.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Carafa Special Malt Type 3 Simcoe, Simcoe, Simcoe, Simcoe, Cascade, Mosaic Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™

hops: Simcoe, Simcoe, Simcoe, Simcoe, Cascade, Mosaic

name: Jack Hammer
tagline: Ruthless India Pale Ale. Hoppy. Bitter. Hoppy.
description: Hopped beyond the point at which IBUs are measurable, only the most hardened palate will get beyond Jack Hammer's intensely resinous pithy bitterness and to the grapefruit, orange zest and dry biscuity malt beyond. You could brew this with less hops, but really, why would you bother?
ingredients: Extra Pale Centennial, Columbus Extract, Centennial, Columbus, Centennial, Columbus, Amarillo, Citra, Simcoe Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Phall Curry, Pork burrito with a habanero and mango chilli salsa, Ginger and grapefruit poundcake
malts: Extra Pale
hops: Centennial, Columbus Extract, Centennial, Columbus, Centennial, Columbus, Amarillo, Citra, Simcoe

name: AB:19
tagline: A Blend of Two Barrel-aged Imperial Saisons.
description: One of the most complex beers we’ve ever attempted. A blend of two barrel-aged Imperial Saisons – one black, one red – which has in turn then been aged in rum barrels, it is an enormous, intricate beer. A baseline of warm, smoky raisin and plum, followed by punchy flavour elements coming to the fore – coconut, mint and blackcurrant. There’s a long undercurrent of treacle toffee, before the finish darkens to liquorice, star anise amidst a touch of honey sweetness.
food_pairing: Game terrine, Spiced fruit cake, Chocolate, cherry and hazelnut mousse

name: Bashah (w/ Stone Brewing Co)
description: Brewed when our good friends from Stone visited in 2009. Black As Sin, Hoppy As Hell - no other beer name has quite hit the nail so squarely on the head. Dark roasted malt makes a beautiful canvas for the savage hop bitterness, pine needles and orange zest.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Chocolate, Carafa Special Malt Type 3 Hercules, Magnum, Magnum, Hercules, Centennial, Amarillo Wyeast 3522 - Belgian Ardennes™
food_pairing: Chocolate crème brûlée with raspberries, Thyme, rosemary and black pepper rubbed roast beef served with fried green beans, Angus beef cheeseburger
malts: Extra Pale, Chocolate, Carafa Special Malt Type 3
hops: Hercules, Magnum, Magnum, Hercules, Centennial, Amarillo

name: Challenger
description: Challenger is known for its herbal and fruity characteristics. When used alone in a beer like IPA is Dead, Challenger brings light woodsy notes, floral hints, and delicate green tea, alongside more recognisable citrus notes. As a dual-purpose hop, it also yields great bittering potential, which is ideal in a dry bitter IPA.
ingredients: Extra Pale - Spring Blend, Caramalt, Crystal 150 Challenger, Challenger, Challenger Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Caramelized onion and steak pie, Chicken Khua Kling (dry Thai curry), Lemon drizzle cake
malts: Extra Pale - Spring Blend, Caramalt, Crystal 150
hops: Challenger, Challenger, Challenger

name: Single Hop Enigma IPA - B-Sides
description: A cheeky play with a new hop on the pilot kit. Expect notes of redcurrant, melon and citrus. An intriguing possibility for the future.
ingredients: Propino Pale Malt Enigma, Enigma, Enigma Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™ & Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Jalapeño poppers with blue cheese dip, T-bone steak with fried onions, Carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
malts: Propino Pale Malt
hops: Enigma, Enigma, Enigma
yeast: Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™ & Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™

name: Chinook - IPA Is Dead
description: 2015 IPA is Dead series. Often used as a combination hop for American Pale Ales and IPAs, Chinook can really shine when left to front a beer all on its own. The main reason for this is that it’s thunderously piney, with a fistful of spice kicked up in your face as you lie on the beach. A true heavyweight of the brewing industry.
ingredients: Extra Pale Chinook, Chinook, Chinook Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Chicken fajita spiced monteray jack quesadillas, Chilli lime and coriander marinated king prawn cocktail, Margarita key lime pie
malts: Extra Pale
hops: Chinook, Chinook, Chinook

name: Konnichiwa Kitsune
description: Named in a slight deviation from our Hello My Name Is series, Konnichiwa Kitsune is a Japanese- inspired, yuzu-infused Imperial IPA, brewed with Amarillo, Cascade and Citra. These punchy new world hops bring orange, grapefruit and lime to back up the yuzu aroma and flavour. Big mandarin notes, balanced against a caramel malt biscuity base.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt Amarillo, Citra, Cascade, Amarillo, Citra, Cascade, Amarillo, Citra, Cascade, Citra, Amarillo, Cascade Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Fresh seared tuna and rocket salad, Lemon meringue pie, Baked chicken with yuzu reduction
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt
hops: Amarillo, Citra, Cascade, Amarillo, Citra, Cascade, Amarillo, Citra, Cascade, Citra, Amarillo, Cascade

name: San Diego Scotch Ale (w/Ballast Point)
tagline: Imperial Scotch Ale With Rum & Raisin.
description: Whisky cask aged with raisins soaked in rum. Warm, chocolatey and boozy with refreshing resinous bitterness and a lingering toasty biscuit background from the malt. Toasted oak comes courtesy of the barrels and spicy, sweet, dark fruit flavours from the rum soaked raisins.
ingredients: Pale Ale - Tipple, Munich, Crystal, Dark Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1 First Gold, Challenger, Amarillo Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Venison stroganoff, Chilli dog, Toffee chocolate cheesecake
malts: Pale Ale - Tipple, Munich, Crystal, Dark Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1
hops: First Gold, Challenger, Amarillo

name: Old World India Pale Ale
description: This recreated the epic IPAs that were sent on monumental ocean voyages from England to India by sea in the 1800s. Medium bodied with a complex malt profile, backed up with intense bitterness and a woodsy, earthy rich English hop character.
ingredients: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Amber, Crystal 150 Bramling Cross, First Gold, Bramling Cross Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Honey glazed ham with spicy roasted carrots, Mature cheddar with spicy chutney, Peach cobbler
malts: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Amber, Crystal 150
hops: Bramling Cross, First Gold, Bramling Cross

name: Dog D
description: Dog D is an extra special brew, marking 8 years of BrewDog. Like Dog A, B & C before it, Dog D is an Imperial Stout with speciality ingredients, only this time we’ve barrel-aged it too. Dog D pours like dark matter into your glass, with a deep tan head. The nose is subtle but powerful, and on the palate, there’s a treacle toffee backbone, supporting the spicy hop flavour and naga chilli heat.
ingredients: Pale Ale, Wheat, Flaked Oats, Dark Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Rye, Brown Chinook, Fuggles, Fuggles, Willamette, Ginger Powder, Honey, Cold Infused Coffee Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Sriracha infused shredded beef, Chipotle steak tacos, Chilli chocolate fondant
malts: Pale Ale, Wheat, Flaked Oats, Dark Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Rye, Brown
hops: Chinook, Fuggles, Fuggles, Willamette, Ginger Powder, Honey, Cold Infused Coffee

name: Simcoe
description: A special release of our IPA is Dead series - IPA is Dead Simoce. Hopped to hell with citrusy bitter and aroma hops from the West Coast of the USA. Bitter, orange, mandarin, floral, this IPA showcases the best the west has to offer.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Munich Simcoe, Simcoe, Simcoe, Simcoe Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Beer roasted chicken, Ham and pineapple pizza, Chocolate cake drizzled with orange
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Munich
hops: Simcoe, Simcoe, Simcoe, Simcoe

name: How To Disappear Completely
description: Jam-packed with two of our favourite hops - Columbus and Centennial, it has 198 (yes one hundred and ninety eight) theoretical IBUs. We use a lot of caramalt, some amber malt and some chocolate malt to give the little beer as much body and mouthfeel as possible and the ability to handle all the hops we threw at it. We think this beer is the world’s first ever Imperial Mild. Imperial in terms of hop profile. An Imperially Hopped Mild. BrewDog’s Imperial Mild. How to Disappear Completely.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Wheat Malt, Munich, Caramalt, Pale Crystal 60, Dark Crystal 350, Amber, Chocolate Centennial, Centennial, Centennial, Columbus, Centennial, Columbus, Centennial, Columbus, Galena, Simcoe Wyeast 3522 - Belgian Ardennes™
food_pairing: Spicy pork sausages with red potato mash, Turnip beef stew with crusty fresh baked bread, Summer berry cheesecake
malts: Extra Pale, Wheat Malt, Munich, Caramalt, Pale Crystal 60, Dark Crystal 350, Amber, Chocolate
hops: Centennial, Centennial, Centennial, Columbus, Centennial, Columbus, Centennial, Columbus, Galena, Simcoe

name: Doodlebug
description: Doodlebug is our fusion of low strength and enormously high tropical hop levels – think a mashup of Hop Fiction and How to Disappear Completely, and you’re almost there. Clocking in at 2.8% ABV, Doodlebug is keg-only and is packed with Amarillo, Chinook and Mosaic; letting fly a hoppy buzzbomb at sub-session-strength.
ingredients: Pilsner, Wheat, Flaked Oats Chinook, Amarillo, Chinook, Mosaic, Amarillo, Chinook, Mosaic Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Lightly curried spiced chickpea dip, Fried calamari with a mild sauce, Lemon sherbet cookies
malts: Pilsner, Wheat, Flaked Oats
hops: Chinook, Amarillo, Chinook, Mosaic, Amarillo, Chinook, Mosaic

name: Vic Secret
description: Piney, citrusy and resinous with herbal notes, Vic Secret is dual-purpose (flavour & bitterness) perfect for brewing up a single hop IPA.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal Vic Secret, Vic Secret, Vic Secret, Vic Secret Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Roasted duck, Gorgonzola and rye nut bread with smoked honey ham, Raspberry coffee cheesecake
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal
hops: Vic Secret, Vic Secret, Vic Secret, Vic Secret

name: All Day Long - Prototype Challenge
description: Prototype Challenge 2014. All Day Long is a mild like no other. This complex, low-alcohol brew was the third of our 2014 Prototypes. Featuring a boatload of seven different speciality malts and some of our favourite hops, this beer is resinous at first, transitioning into something akin to bitter orange marmalade spread onto a thick bread crust. This is for everyone who said BrewDog would never brew a mild...
ingredients: Caramalt Columbus, Cascade, Centennial, Columbus, Ahtanum, Centennial, Cascade, Amarillo Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Chunky orange marmalade on toast, Prawn toast with sweet chilli sauce, Lemon tart
malts: Caramalt
hops: Columbus, Cascade, Centennial, Columbus, Ahtanum, Centennial, Cascade, Amarillo

name: Nuns With Guns
description: A dry-hopped Session Pilsner. At 4.2% this amber-hued lager packs a malty punch with toasty Munich character and a light caramel sweetness. From here, things take a sharp turn towards the hoppy flavour, with some serious US citrus packed classic hops.
ingredients: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich Cascade, Cascade, Centennial, Chinook, Amarillo, Chinook, Amarillo, Cascade Wyeast 2007 - Pilsen Lager™
food_pairing: Falafel and hummus pitta wrap, Bratwurst with spicy relish, Strawberry tart
malts: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich
hops: Cascade, Cascade, Centennial, Chinook, Amarillo, Chinook, Amarillo, Cascade

name: Atlantic IPA Ale
description: Like IPA historically would have been. Part of this beer was aged on a fishing boat in an oak cask and released as "Atlantic IPA".
ingredients: Extra Pale, Amber, Crystal First Gold, East Kent Goldings, Fuggles, Bramling Cross, Goldings Safale US-05
food_pairing: Smoked venison sausage, Very mature Cheddar, Fettucine alfredo
malts: Extra Pale, Amber, Crystal
hops: First Gold, East Kent Goldings, Fuggles, Bramling Cross, Goldings

name: Tactical Nuclear Penguin
description: This beer is about pushing the boundaries, it is about taking innovation in beer to a whole new level. Dark and decadent, plum, treacle and roast coffee are amplified beyond any stout you've had before.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Dark Crystal, Chocolate, Roasted Barley Chinook, Galena, Chinook, Galena, Galena, First Gold, Chinook WLP099 - Super High Gravity Ale
food_pairing: Lobster thermidor, Pan fried Foie Gras, Vanilla bean white chocolate
malts: Extra Pale, Dark Crystal, Chocolate, Roasted Barley
hops: Chinook, Galena, Chinook, Galena, Galena, First Gold, Chinook

name: Jasmine IPA
description: This has big floral aromas backed up with some of our favourite fruity hop flavours. Bitter, bright and refreshing, our Jasmine IPA is a perfect spring beer for drinking outside (under a patio heater, with a pair of gloves on).
ingredients: Pale Ale, Munich, Rye, Wheat Motueka, Amarillo, Motueka, Jasmine, Motueka, Jasmine, Amarillo Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Chicken satay, Thai fishcakes, Honey and almond sponge cake
malts: Pale Ale, Munich, Rye, Wheat
hops: Motueka, Amarillo, Motueka, Jasmine, Motueka, Jasmine, Amarillo

name: Lichtenstein Pale Ale
description: Dry-hopped with some of our hop heroes, bringing incredibly fruity aromas of zesty orange, pithy grapefruit, pungent pine and resin, backed up with spicy, toasty malt flavours of toffee, biscuit, rye bread and toast crust.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Crystal 150, Munich, Rye Centennial, Simcoe, Cascade, Amarillo, Simcoe, Cascade, Amarillo, Simcoe, Cascade, Centennial, Amarillo Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Spicy fish tacos, Bacon mac 'n' cheese, Pear crumble
malts: Extra Pale, Crystal 150, Munich, Rye
hops: Centennial, Simcoe, Cascade, Amarillo, Simcoe, Cascade, Amarillo, Simcoe, Cascade, Centennial, Amarillo

name: Paradox Jura
description: Paradox. Reloaded. In 2011 we put Paradox into high gear to create an Imperial Stout destined for ageing. Loaded with dark roasted malts for a full bodied, toasted background, an array of bitter, earthy and resinous hops, and brewed with oats for a bold mouthfeel. This beer is the perfect canvas for barrel ageing.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich, Flaked Oats, Dark Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Carafa Special Malt Type 3 Columbus, Columbus, Saaz, First Gold Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Smoked cured beef, Smoked aubergine tapenade with rye bread, Beer affogato - 1/3 glass of Paradox with a scoop of vanilla ice cream
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Munich, Flaked Oats, Dark Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Carafa Special Malt Type 3
hops: Columbus, Columbus, Saaz, First Gold

name: AB:11
tagline: Black Barley Wine With Ginger, Raspberries, Chipotle Peppers.
description: AB:11 is an Imperial Black Barley Wine brewed with ginger, black raspberries and chipotle peppers. A 12.8% rollercoaster of ginger zestiness and chipotle smokiness, all bound together with dark berry tartness and the decadent residual body of a Black Barley Wine.
ingredients: Extra Pale - Spring Blend, Caramalt, Munich, Amber, Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1 Columbus, Columbus, Saaz, Columbus, Ginger Powder Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Steak taquitos with spicy mole sauce, Herb roasted duck with a fruit sauce, Dark chocolate and chilli flourless cake
malts: Extra Pale - Spring Blend, Caramalt, Munich, Amber, Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1
hops: Columbus, Columbus, Saaz, Columbus, Ginger Powder

name: Hello My Name is Sonja (w/ Evil Twin)
description: Brewed in collaboration with Jeppe from Evil Twin Brewing (and named after his mum), this Double IPA is big on fruity flavours. Single hopped with Mosaic for lots of tropical, passion fruit and citrus flavours. Loaded with well over 100kg of blueberries, the original was one super fruity hop bomb.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Wheat Mosaic, Mosaic, Mosaic, Blueberries, Mosaic Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Lamb chops with a blueberry reduction, Cured ham and strong mulled cheddar board, Warm blueberry pie
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Wheat
hops: Mosaic, Mosaic, Mosaic, Blueberries, Mosaic

name: Interstellar
description: Interstellar is a Red Rye IPA with spicy rye flavours from the malt and with great all-round spicy, fruity and earthy hop aromas from the use of Willamette and Amarillo.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Rye, Crystal 150, Dark Crystal, Acidulated Malt Magnum, Willamette, Amarillo, Willamette, Amarillo, Amarillo, Willamette Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Oak chip smoked salmon, Sticky spicy barbecue ribs, Scottish tablet
malts: Extra Pale, Rye, Crystal 150, Dark Crystal, Acidulated Malt
hops: Magnum, Willamette, Amarillo, Willamette, Amarillo, Amarillo, Willamette

name: Punk IPA 2007 - 2010
tagline: Post Modern Classic. Spiky. Tropical. Hoppy.
description: Our flagship beer that kick started the craft beer revolution. This is James and Martin's original take on an American IPA, subverted with punchy New Zealand hops. Layered with new world hops to create an all-out riot of grapefruit, pineapple and lychee before a spiky, mouth-puckering bitter finish.
ingredients: Extra Pale Ahtanum, Chinook, Crystal, Chinook, Ahtanum, Chinook, Crystal, Motueka Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Spicy carne asada with a pico de gallo sauce, Shredded chicken tacos with a mango chilli lime salsa, Cheesecake with a passion fruit swirl sauce
malts: Extra Pale
hops: Ahtanum, Chinook, Crystal, Chinook, Ahtanum, Chinook, Crystal, Motueka

name: Blitz Berliner Weisse
description: Our sour recipe for all fruit Blitz beers uses a process called kettle souring. In this we steep a bag of malt in the wort to allow the bacteria to grow in it.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Wheat Magnum Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Grilled salmon with a light lemon sauce, Lobster bisque, Cheesecake with raspberry (or peach/passion fruit) sauce
malts: Extra Pale, Wheat
hops: Magnum

name: Hardkogt IPA
tagline: A Special Double IPA For Our Danish Friends.
description: Brewed for the beer maniacs in Denmark, this Double IPA quivered with kumquat, kiwi and orange pith all held together with a honeycomb malt body.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Crystal 150, Caramalt Columbus, Columbus, Centennial, Simcoe, Columbus, Centennial, Simcoe, Columbus, Centennial, Simcoe Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Thick cut salami pieces on tiger bread, Chilli spiced pork pie, Poached pear and blue cheese crumble
malts: Extra Pale, Crystal 150, Caramalt
hops: Columbus, Columbus, Centennial, Simcoe, Columbus, Centennial, Simcoe, Columbus, Centennial, Simcoe

name: Hello My Name Is Holy Moose
description: Cloudberry, lingonberry, blueberry and sea buckthorn meld with citrusy hops in an intensely sweet, fruity and floral aroma, with toasty malt notes and tropical fruit bursts. This bitter, resinous IPA follows up with a lemony punch in the mouth - cherry and blueberry sourness takes this pithy pale ale in a new direction before a long, dry finish.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Carared Citra, Challenger, Centennial, Citra, Citra, Mosaic, Bramling Cross, Centennial, Citra, Bramling Cross, Mosaic, Nelson Sauvin, Simcoe Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Warms goats cheese salad, Trifle or chocolate cake
malts: Extra Pale, Carared
hops: Citra, Challenger, Centennial, Citra, Citra, Mosaic, Bramling Cross, Centennial, Citra, Bramling Cross, Mosaic, Nelson Sauvin, Simcoe

name: Catherine's Pony (w/ Beavertown)
description: An Imperial Smoked Porter with a nose like gooseberries and blueberries, stuffed with coffee, covered in chocolate and toasted on a campfire by the beach, Catherine’s Pony is robust and imposing with a herculean mouthfeel. Rich and smooth with roasted smoky flavours battling for prominence over the assertive bitterness. A satisfying hoppiness rounds off the palate.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Carafa Special Malt Type 2, Crystal 150, Smoked Warminster Magnum, Cascade, Fuggles, First Gold, Coffee Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Flame grilled steak, Venison and Winter vegetable stew, Maple bacon chocolate cupcakes
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Carafa Special Malt Type 2, Crystal 150, Smoked Warminster
hops: Magnum, Cascade, Fuggles, First Gold, Coffee

name: Moshi Moshi 15
description: A riot of C-hops, with layers of grapefruit, lime zest, pine needles, freshly cut grass, pungent resin, layered up on toasty malt with a touch of caramel sweetness.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Munich, Crystal 150, Caramalt Columbus, Columbus, Centennial, Columbus, Centennial, Columbus, Centennial, Cascade Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Spicy Vietnamese vermicelli salad, Spicy fish tacos with mango chilli, Banana bread
malts: Extra Pale, Munich, Crystal 150, Caramalt
hops: Columbus, Columbus, Centennial, Columbus, Centennial, Columbus, Centennial, Cascade

name: AB:01
description: Made with the yeast from a bottle of Westvleteren 12, aged with vanilla beans. Only available in 375ml bottles. Limited to 3200 bottles. The first in our Abstrakt series.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Wheat, Munich Saaz, Saaz, Styrian Goldings Westvleteren 12 (recovered from a bottle)
food_pairing: Baked brown butter lobster, Apple crumble and custard, Coffee carrot cake
malts: Extra Pale, Wheat, Munich
hops: Saaz, Saaz, Styrian Goldings

name: Alice Porter
description: First brewed in 2010, Alice Porter returned as a seasonal in 2015. The beer was originally created and brewed for (real life) Alice Porter’s impending nuptials to the Beer King of Leeds, Matt Gorecki.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Munich, Crystal 150, Special W, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Flaked Oats, Torrified Wheat Magnum, First Gold, First Gold, Sorachi Ace Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Applewood cheddar bacon beef burger, Roasted garlic camembert, Parmesan truffles
malts: Extra Pale, Munich, Crystal 150, Special W, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Flaked Oats, Torrified Wheat
hops: Magnum, First Gold, First Gold, Sorachi Ace

name: Double IPA - Russian Doll
description: The levels of hops vary throughout the range. We love hops, so all four beers are big, bitter badasses, but by tweaking the amount of each hop used later in the boil and during dry- hopping, we can balance the malty backbone with some unexpected flavours. Simcoe is used in the whirlpool for all four beers, and yet still lends different characters to each.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal Centennial, Cascade, Citra, Simcoe, Citra, Cascade, Simcoe, Cascade, Centennial, Citra Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Strong cheddar fondue, Pork chops with spicy orange marmalade, Rich crème brûlée
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal
hops: Centennial, Cascade, Citra, Simcoe, Citra, Cascade, Simcoe, Cascade, Centennial, Citra

name: Waimea - IPA Is Dead
description: Waimea has a new world flavour, infusing unique fresh crushed citrus aroma and flavour notes into this IPA - think intense fresh tangelo, citrus fruit and pine needle characteristics. There is a huge depth of flavour with astringent gooseberry balanced against the robust malt base.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Munich Waimea, Waimea, Waimea, Waimea Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Hot spiced barbecue chicken wings, Orange sesame chicken, Chocolate fondue with fruit
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Dark Crystal, Munich
hops: Waimea, Waimea, Waimea, Waimea

name: Dog C
description: Our anniversary stout was based on AB:04, one of our most sought after beers ever. This beer is slightly different each year, with subtle variations coming into play purely down to environmental and fermentation factors. What doesn't change is the rich dark chocolate, bitter coffee and chilli warmth of this monumental stout.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Wheat, Flaked Oats, Dark Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Rye, Honey Chinook, Cascade, Fuggles, Coffee, Fuggles, Coffee Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Blackened cajun beef, Blue cheese, Flourless chocolate cheesecake
malts: Extra Pale, Wheat, Flaked Oats, Dark Crystal, Carafa Special Malt Type 1, Carafa Special Malt Type 3, Rye, Honey
hops: Chinook, Cascade, Fuggles, Coffee, Fuggles, Coffee

name: Bitch Please (w/ 3 Floyds)
description: This limited edition American Barley Wine was brewed in collaboration with 3 Floyds Brewery. This beer had all the warm, boozy and smoky aspects of an Islay Scotch whisky with the sweet malt and devastatingly bitter attributes of a barley wine. Peat smoke features prominently, backed up with a complex fruity hop profile.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Pinhead Oats, Carahell, CaraAroma, Roasted Malt, Peated Malt Green Bullet, Motueka, Pacific Gem, Nelson Sauvin Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Stilton Blue featured cheese platter, Dark bitter chocolate torte, Scotch bonnet beef chilli
malts: Extra Pale, Pinhead Oats, Carahell, CaraAroma, Roasted Malt, Peated Malt
hops: Green Bullet, Motueka, Pacific Gem, Nelson Sauvin

name: Cascade, Centennial & Willamette IPA - B-Sides
description: An experiment in balancing hops on the pilot kit. Grapefruit, orange and resin to the fore.
ingredients: Propino Pale Malt, Dextrin Malt, Flaked Oats Centennial, Cascade, Willamette Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™ & Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™
food_pairing: Cauliflower pakora with mango chutney, Penne with tomato and smoked cheese, Salted caramel ice cream and peanuts
malts: Propino Pale Malt, Dextrin Malt, Flaked Oats
hops: Centennial, Cascade, Willamette
yeast: Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™ & Wyeast 1272 - American Ale II™

name: Shareholder Black IPA 2011
description: Brewed as part of the shareholder brewday at our Fraserburgh brewery. Massively dry hopped and aged on toasted oak chips, this IPA was a riot of lemon, vanilla and roasted malt.
ingredients: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150, Carafa Special Malt Type 1 Amarillo, Columbus, Chinook, Columbus, Cascade, Centennial, Centennial, Cascade, Amarillo, Chinook Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Classic American cheeseburger, Chilli chocolate bars
malts: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150, Carafa Special Malt Type 1
hops: Amarillo, Columbus, Chinook, Columbus, Cascade, Centennial, Centennial, Cascade, Amarillo, Chinook

name: Black Jacques
tagline: Red Wine Barrel-Aged Imperial Black Saison.
description: A Black Saison, brewed with oats and wheat for a silky mouthfeel, Spicy hops and Carafa Malt for colour, then aged in red wine barrels. On the nose there's cola, chocolate, coffee, mint humbug, warming oak, and spice. The myriad flavours touch on treacle, ripe banana, espresso, brandy, and a clean herbal warmth.
ingredients: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Wheat, Flaked Malted Oats, Crystal 150, Carafa Special Malt Type 3 Bravo, Bravo, Mt.Hood, Bravo, Mt.Hood Wyeast 3711 - French Saison™
food_pairing: Cured Spanish ham, Steak pasty, Black cherry tart
malts: Extra Pale, Caramalt, Wheat, Flaked Malted Oats, Crystal 150, Carafa Special Malt Type 3
hops: Bravo, Bravo, Mt.Hood, Bravo, Mt.Hood

name: International Arms Race (w/ Flying Dog)
description: The International Arms Race was a new type of battle collaboration between hardcore American craft brewery Flying Dog and BrewDog. Both breweries attempted to brew an IPA with absolutely no hops.
ingredients: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150 Bay Leaves, Rosemary, Elderflower Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Rosemary and thyme grilled chicken, Light vegetable and herb soup with toasted rye bread, Earl Grey ice cream with a lavender sauce
malts: Maris Otter Extra Pale, Caramalt, Crystal 150
hops: Bay Leaves, Rosemary, Elderflower

name: Sunshine On Rye - B-Sides
description: A Pilot Brew "Sunshine on Rye" uses loads of spicy malt and coriander to play nice with an inhuman amount of hops!
ingredients: Extra Pale, Rye, Caramalt Amarillo, Citra, Simcoe, Amarillo, Citra, Simcoe, Amarillo, Citra, Simcoe, Nelson Sauvin Wyeast 1056 - American Ale™
food_pairing: Jerk spiced goat, Tonkotsu Ramen, Gingerbread
malts: Extra Pale, Rye, Caramalt
hops: Amarillo, Citra, Simcoe, Amarillo, Citra, Simcoe, Amarillo, Citra, Simcoe, Nelson Sauvin

name: Stereo Wolf Stout - Prototype Challenge
description: Roasty, dark and complex, Stereo Wolf is a 5.2% ABV Stout brewed with a cacophony of hop-driven fruit and spice. Dark chocolate stalks alongside the resonating bitterness, through to Stereo Wolf’s lingering dry finish. When tasting, Hinterland reveals itself as the beer moves from cellar temperature to something warmer, yielding all of the above plus dried fruit, rich ganache and ending on a resoundingly warming  nish redolent of chocolate liqueur or plum brandy. Aged in Bourbon Casks.

Monk Hammer is the first of our super-charge hyped up hybrids. A dark cloaked holy man packing an unholy punch. Belgian yeast and American hops untie on a cardinal scale. Steel yourself for biblical volumes of grapefruit, bow your head for a wave of spicy, fruity yeast character, then cross yourself for the bitterest of bitter finishes. To celebrate this fetish we’re heroing our favourites in single hopped limited releases. No also starring, no extras, no compromise. The Hop is the Hero. A biscuity malty backbone builds to resinous pine with explosive citrus notes, culminating in a mango hit and a long bitter finish. This is pure Hop fusion, imploding with sensory overload.
